WEBVTT

00:25.111 --> 00:29.560
("RIP HER TO SHREDS"
BY BLONDIE PLAYS)

00:31.416 --> 00:32.505
(BOTTLES RATTLE)

00:33.893 --> 00:34.895
♪ Hey ♪

00:35.989 --> 00:37.595
♪ Here she comes now ♪

00:40.708 --> 00:42.742
♪ Oh, you know her ♪

00:42.767 --> 00:44.704
♪ Would you look at that hair ♪

00:44.729 --> 00:46.684
♪ Yeah, you know her ♪

00:47.006 --> 00:48.761
♪ Check out those shoes ♪

00:48.786 --> 00:50.849
♪ She looks like
She stepped out of ♪

00:50.874 --> 00:53.810
♪ The middle
Of somebody's blues ♪

00:56.289 --> 00:57.965
♪ She looks like
The Sunday comics ♪

00:57.990 --> 00:59.005
DONOVAN: (QUIETLY) Linda.

01:00.220 --> 01:01.421
♪ She thinks she's-- ♪

01:01.446 --> 01:02.573
Earth to Linda.

01:02.598 --> 01:04.764
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:04.789 --> 01:05.854
Oh.

01:06.603 --> 01:07.685
(MUSIC FADES)

01:08.328 --> 01:09.604
Still working
on the company report?

01:09.629 --> 01:11.690
Uh, I finished that last week.

01:11.784 --> 01:14.442
I was just working on
some projections for next month.

01:14.688 --> 01:15.942
You include
last year's numbers?

01:15.967 --> 01:17.285
Mm-hmm.
All index-correlated

01:17.315 --> 01:19.623
with next year's
estimated quarterlies included.

01:20.613 --> 01:22.871
- (CHUCKLES) You're amazing.
- Oh.

01:23.089 --> 01:24.891
God, I have so much trouble
with this stuff.

01:25.291 --> 01:27.360
All right. They're all waiting.

01:27.385 --> 01:30.021
(INHALES)
Showtime. I'm right behind ya.

01:30.105 --> 01:31.807
- Oh.
- Oh.

01:31.832 --> 01:33.604
No, they shrunk it down
to a smaller group.

01:34.087 --> 01:36.727
I'm actually just,
uh, dropping it off.

01:39.499 --> 01:41.785
I-I put the numbers together.

01:42.195 --> 01:43.585
They told me they wanted me
in the room

01:43.610 --> 01:44.956
in case there were
any questions.

01:44.998 --> 01:47.100
Questions.
Yeah, I don't really know.

01:47.694 --> 01:50.618
I mean, you know how it's been
around here lately, Linda,

01:50.643 --> 01:51.678
it's just all...

01:52.011 --> 01:53.112
...up in the air.

01:54.995 --> 01:56.051
Yeah.

01:56.076 --> 01:58.712
But don't worry. They'll know
who did the heavy lifting.

01:58.898 --> 02:01.133
(INHALES)
Your name is right on top.

02:03.503 --> 02:04.535
Okay.

02:05.397 --> 02:06.932
- Okay.
- Thanks.

02:07.374 --> 02:08.408
Good luck in there.

02:08.995 --> 02:10.215
(INHALES)

02:11.723 --> 02:12.723
Well...

02:13.312 --> 02:15.909
Guess that old
elevator to success

02:15.934 --> 02:17.735
is out of order again, huh?

02:18.698 --> 02:20.672
- What?
- (CHUCKLES) Oh.

02:20.697 --> 02:23.795
I was just saying, we're gonna
have to keep taking the stairs.

02:24.217 --> 02:26.332
One step at a time.

02:27.932 --> 02:29.022
CHASE: Oi!

02:29.047 --> 02:31.022
- Chase!
- Oh. Hey, what's up?

02:31.704 --> 02:33.295
- 'Sup?
- Uh...

02:33.392 --> 02:35.876
A few of us after work
are hitting Milly and Al's for--

02:35.901 --> 02:36.974
- So down.
- Oh!

02:36.999 --> 02:40.697
(CHUCKLES) Milly and--
That's the best karaoke in town.

02:40.900 --> 02:42.201
- CHASE: Yeah, it is.
- Could really go for a song

02:42.226 --> 02:43.434
and a drink tonight.

02:43.903 --> 02:47.222
My go-to is
"One Way Or Another."

02:48.775 --> 02:49.810
RIVER: Uh...

02:49.835 --> 02:50.777
- Is that...
- LINDA: No?

02:50.802 --> 02:52.090
- No.
- Blondie?

02:52.183 --> 02:54.111
- Debbie Harry? Oh, man.
- No.

02:54.143 --> 02:54.911
- All right.
- CHASE: All right.

02:54.936 --> 02:56.530
"I'm gonna get ya, get ya,
get ya, get ya."

02:56.555 --> 02:57.623
Hey!

02:57.648 --> 02:59.221
You gotta Google her.

02:59.605 --> 03:01.440
Um, do you have a go-to, or...

03:02.095 --> 03:03.537
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

03:14.400 --> 03:15.484
(CLEARS THROAT)

03:20.807 --> 03:21.980
(PAPER CRUMPLES)

03:23.189 --> 03:25.791
Here is the company review
I prepared.

03:26.492 --> 03:29.083
Lost a lot of sleep putting
this little baby together.

03:29.108 --> 03:31.806
(CHUCKLES) But no rest
for the wicked, am I right?

03:31.831 --> 03:32.866
(SIGHS)

03:40.786 --> 03:43.288
LINDA: So get this.
After all that work,

03:43.665 --> 03:44.945
I didn't even get to go
to the meeting.

03:44.970 --> 03:45.991
(SCOFFS)

03:46.016 --> 03:49.306
- (CHOPPING)
- I swear, Sweetie, sometimes...

03:49.788 --> 03:51.991
Yeah, I'm still sitting
with the assistants.

03:52.016 --> 03:54.404
But, all that changes tomorrow.

03:54.587 --> 03:55.657
When Bradley--

03:56.303 --> 04:00.460
Mr. Preston officially
takes over for his father.

04:00.485 --> 04:01.529
(CHIRPS)

04:01.554 --> 04:04.230
Yep. His father said,
right in front of him,

04:04.255 --> 04:06.629
that I was next in line for VP.

04:06.705 --> 04:09.102
So, he knows my value
to the company.

04:10.596 --> 04:13.227
And he's good-looking,
and he's single

04:13.252 --> 04:15.509
and charming,
and blah, blah, blah.

04:15.534 --> 04:17.790
And I told you how flirty he was
with me at the Christmas party.

04:17.815 --> 04:18.816
Whoo!

04:19.905 --> 04:20.906
But...

04:21.467 --> 04:23.284
That has nothing to do
with anything.

04:23.309 --> 04:25.211
(CHEWING LOUDLY)

04:25.271 --> 04:26.699
We just need to focus on...

04:27.814 --> 04:30.620
the new office, the new title...

04:33.386 --> 04:35.017
...maybe that bigger apartment.

04:36.997 --> 04:38.805
(SNIFFS, GIGGLES)

04:39.612 --> 04:41.380
We're gonna
spread our wings a little.

04:43.469 --> 04:44.787
It's not over for us.

04:46.192 --> 04:47.450
(WHISPERS)
Best is yet to come.

04:48.102 --> 04:49.688
(PARAKEET CHIRPS)

04:49.889 --> 04:51.228
LINDA: Well, exactly.

04:53.493 --> 04:54.529
We deserve it.

05:01.600 --> 05:02.599
You deserve it.

05:04.268 --> 05:05.304
Hmm?

05:09.794 --> 05:11.308
Up you go. Come on.

05:16.361 --> 05:17.381
(CHIRPS)

05:17.406 --> 05:18.432
Mmm.

05:20.713 --> 05:21.801
(TWEETS)

05:22.294 --> 05:23.492
We deserve it.

05:25.624 --> 05:26.662
Mmm!

05:26.799 --> 05:28.401
It's time. Okay.

05:31.290 --> 05:33.437
JEFF: Who'll have
what it takes to outwit...

05:33.462 --> 05:34.855
- Outplay, outlast.
- ...outplay, and outlast...

05:34.880 --> 05:36.041
all the rest.

05:36.100 --> 05:40.570
- This is Survivor.
- (TRIBAL HORN BLOWS)

05:40.600 --> 05:43.545
If Kishan gets voted off
tonight, I swear to God.

05:44.603 --> 05:46.016
(CHIRPING)

05:46.074 --> 05:47.102
That's what I'm saying.

05:53.811 --> 05:55.947
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

05:57.922 --> 06:00.100
Ladies and gentlemen, may
I have your attention please?

06:00.506 --> 06:04.137
I'd like to present to you your
new president, Bradley Preston.

06:04.411 --> 06:06.989
(APPLAUSE)

06:09.101 --> 06:10.498
This is Marshall, IT...

06:10.523 --> 06:12.558
BRADLEY: Marshall, look forward
to working with you.

06:12.583 --> 06:14.464
- FRANKLIN: Sonja. Sales.
- Nice to meet you, Mr. Preston.

06:14.523 --> 06:17.203
- Mmm.
- And finally, Sierra, Marketing.

06:17.228 --> 06:18.430
All right, sit down,
sit down, sit down.

06:18.455 --> 06:19.723
Okay, everybody back to work.

06:20.713 --> 06:22.645
Got a few things to talk to you
about in the office, okay?

06:22.670 --> 06:23.544
BRADLEY: Sure.

06:23.569 --> 06:24.756
FRANKLIN: Soon as we can,
we gotta get you--

06:24.781 --> 06:25.927
- Mr. Preston!
- Hi!

06:26.626 --> 06:28.296
Call me Bradley.
Nice to meet you.

06:28.501 --> 06:30.231
Oh, um...

06:30.403 --> 06:34.019
Linda Liddle.
We spoke at the Christmas party.

06:34.600 --> 06:36.202
- Um...
- Oh. That's right.

06:36.227 --> 06:37.766
No, yes. Of course.

06:37.791 --> 06:39.225
Of course,
it's great to see you again.

06:39.250 --> 06:41.725
Yes. You, too. And I'm so sorry
about your father.

06:41.750 --> 06:44.453
- I appreciate that.
- He was a very admirable man.

06:44.478 --> 06:45.520
He really
took me under his wing.

06:45.545 --> 06:47.080
- Yes. Me, too.
- Um...

06:47.286 --> 06:51.484
But I am so excited about this
opportunity to help you execute

06:51.509 --> 06:52.822
(ECHOING)
...your strategic vision

06:52.847 --> 06:55.555
and lead this company
into a new era of, um...

06:56.594 --> 06:57.814
(SMACKS LIPS)
Um...

06:59.419 --> 07:00.457
Era of success.

07:01.487 --> 07:03.756
- Exactly.
- Well, I hope to do just that.

07:03.817 --> 07:04.903
It's gonna be
a lot of work though.

07:04.928 --> 07:06.125
Big shoes to fill, right?

07:06.979 --> 07:08.291
Gonna need
all the help I can get.

07:08.627 --> 07:10.068
(SCATTERED CHUCKLES)

07:10.395 --> 07:13.100
Well, and I have
the right shoes already.

07:13.140 --> 07:14.586
- (CHUCKLES)
- What's that?

07:15.007 --> 07:18.192
I call these my Liddle Mules.

07:18.291 --> 07:20.785
Had these girls a long time.
A lot of miles on them.

07:20.839 --> 07:24.343
And they can carry any load
you throw their way.

07:24.504 --> 07:26.039
- Yeah. I gotta get to it.
- Okay.

07:26.064 --> 07:27.110
Okay.

07:27.135 --> 07:28.570
Oh, my gosh. Look at your shoes.

07:28.595 --> 07:31.600
Those are fancy-pants.

07:31.690 --> 07:34.159
Just don't step
in any puddles, right?

07:34.393 --> 07:35.729
I'm sorry, I didn't catch that.

07:36.482 --> 07:38.105
(WHISPERS)
Don't step in any puddles.

07:39.698 --> 07:41.327
- I'll try to avoid that.
- Okay.

07:42.202 --> 07:44.447
(WHISPERS)
All right. Get back to work.

07:46.493 --> 07:48.513
All right, gentlemen. Let's get
our P's and Q's in order.

07:48.902 --> 07:51.118
Barbara, lovely to see you.
Can you hold my calls?

07:53.706 --> 07:54.734
No, that went well.

07:55.093 --> 07:56.163
You just wanna go with

07:56.188 --> 07:58.516
the, uh, consulting firm's
recommendations?

07:59.591 --> 08:00.641
That's funny, right?

08:00.666 --> 08:02.997
A consulting firm
hiring a consulting firm.

08:03.022 --> 08:04.617
- What is that?
- What?

08:04.703 --> 08:05.604
This.

08:06.004 --> 08:07.005
I don't know.

08:07.893 --> 08:08.896
- Smell it.
- No.

08:08.981 --> 08:10.249
- Yes.
- No.

08:10.274 --> 08:11.282
Yes.

08:14.900 --> 08:15.904
(SIGHS)

08:19.205 --> 08:20.240
Smell it.

08:22.822 --> 08:25.298
(SNIFFS)

08:25.912 --> 08:26.916
Tuna fish.

08:28.093 --> 08:29.260
Tuna fish.

08:31.591 --> 08:32.988
It's that disgusting woman.

08:33.312 --> 08:36.213
The one who accosted me
with Payless orthopedics.

08:36.238 --> 08:39.110
Linda Liddle. Your father
promised her a promotion.

08:39.278 --> 08:41.364
- From manager to vice president.
- Did he?

08:41.487 --> 08:43.304
A big bump in title and salary.

08:43.529 --> 08:44.797
- Yeah.
- She's been waiting for it.

08:44.822 --> 08:46.803
Right. Well.
Donovan's getting that job.

08:47.894 --> 08:50.791
Your father relied on Linda.
Real workhorse.

08:50.883 --> 08:52.285
I dump everything on her.

08:52.344 --> 08:53.779
BRADLEY:
Does it look like I give a shit?

08:53.900 --> 08:55.257
It doesn't, right?
'Cause I don't.

08:55.488 --> 08:57.812
My father's not here anymore.
It's Donovan's.

08:58.778 --> 09:00.757
Plus, I already told them.
And move her.

09:00.782 --> 09:02.250
Satellite office, maybe.

09:02.281 --> 09:04.883
Somewhere far.
She makes me sick.

09:05.197 --> 09:06.207
(SHUDDERS)

09:07.272 --> 09:08.807
We have Bangkok coming up.

09:09.328 --> 09:11.603
And we haven't even
cracked Appendix-D.

09:11.910 --> 09:13.911
Donovan will drown on his own.

09:14.394 --> 09:15.817
The whole thing could fall apart
without her.

09:15.842 --> 09:17.377
(SARCASTICALLY)
Okay. Fine.

09:17.897 --> 09:19.011
Bring her.

09:19.691 --> 09:21.762
She'll get Don-O up to speed.
And then we'll ship her out.

09:21.827 --> 09:25.690
- (INDISTINCT CHATTER)
- (RAPID TYPING)

09:25.886 --> 09:28.103
(MEN LAUGHING)

09:30.683 --> 09:32.605
Wait, wait, wait,
this is funny...

09:32.630 --> 09:34.290
(STAMMERING)

09:34.387 --> 09:35.550
That little shake...

09:36.501 --> 09:37.795
- Whoop.
- (LAUGHS)

09:40.599 --> 09:42.120
All right. Ah.

09:42.802 --> 09:45.863
- Gotta get back to work.
- (LAUGHS)

09:46.693 --> 09:49.789
All right. Back to work.
(SIGHS)

09:50.389 --> 09:52.853
Well, they seem kind of chummy.

09:52.878 --> 09:55.705
Well, yeah, he's being promoted
to vice president.

09:56.415 --> 09:58.325
Sorry. I'm sorry, what?

09:58.350 --> 10:00.086
Yeah, I'm typing
the company-wide email

10:00.111 --> 10:01.112
about it right now.

10:01.467 --> 10:03.602
- Oh, tell me you're kidding.
- Mm-mm-mm.

10:03.627 --> 10:06.088
I literally looked
at his LinkedIn profile,

10:06.113 --> 10:08.549
and they were in
the same frat in college.

10:08.608 --> 10:10.990
And they play golf together.
So, duh.

10:11.882 --> 10:14.112
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

10:31.176 --> 10:32.381
Linda, what the heck?

10:32.885 --> 10:35.811
Uh, my final question would be,
how above and beyond

10:35.836 --> 10:37.902
would you be willing
to go for me?

10:37.927 --> 10:39.729
- (KNOCKS ON GLASS)
- Yes?

10:39.792 --> 10:40.926
Mr. Preston?

10:41.186 --> 10:42.221
I'm in a meeting.

10:42.294 --> 10:44.322
I'm sorry. I just need
a moment of your time.

10:44.897 --> 10:46.065
- Right, well, I'm--
- Please.

10:47.607 --> 10:48.641
Please.

10:48.727 --> 10:49.731
Sure.

10:50.349 --> 10:51.405
We'll be in touch.

10:52.485 --> 10:54.328
Thanks for coming in.
(COUGHS)

10:56.301 --> 10:57.308
LINDA: Sorry.

10:59.384 --> 11:00.764
Sorry to barge in like this--

11:00.789 --> 11:03.230
Nope. Open door policy.
What's up?

11:03.269 --> 11:05.725
Uh-- Well, I just heard
about the job--

11:05.750 --> 11:07.344
You're unhappy about
not getting the promotion.

11:08.114 --> 11:09.124
Well, yes.

11:09.387 --> 11:10.450
Yeah. Okay.

11:10.963 --> 11:13.187
Yes, respectfully, uh...

11:14.106 --> 11:16.041
Donovan has been here
for six months,

11:16.066 --> 11:18.523
and I have been here
for seven years, and-and--

11:19.411 --> 11:20.493
I hear you.

11:21.000 --> 11:23.948
Let's talk it out.
Come in, close the door.

11:24.609 --> 11:25.777
Let's talk about it.

11:28.320 --> 11:29.320
BRADLEY: Hmm?

11:33.532 --> 11:34.694
Please, sit.

11:37.896 --> 11:39.131
(SIGHS)

11:41.393 --> 11:44.630
Now, I'm going to be frank
with you. If that's all right.

11:45.291 --> 11:47.883
I know that you are great
with numbers.

11:48.393 --> 11:50.369
- Kind of a savant.
- (CHUCKLES)

11:50.416 --> 11:52.046
- Right?
- I am good with numbers, yes.

11:52.071 --> 11:54.273
Yes, and I've carefully
reviewed a lot of that work,

11:54.298 --> 11:57.278
and it is impressive,
so that's the positive.

11:57.303 --> 11:58.319
Thank you.

11:58.503 --> 12:00.427
But, I...

12:01.300 --> 12:03.468
...don't see you as being
somebody who's ready

12:03.493 --> 12:05.929
for an executive position
quite yet.

12:10.269 --> 12:11.312
Why?

12:11.477 --> 12:13.538
I guess, as a VP,
I would need somebody

12:13.563 --> 12:15.932
who is more of a people person.

12:16.688 --> 12:20.716
You know, somebody by my side
who is well-liked.

12:21.399 --> 12:22.702
Who can charm a room.

12:23.088 --> 12:25.192
Who can make a deal.

12:25.217 --> 12:26.332
Somebody who golfs.

12:27.405 --> 12:28.461
Does that make sense?

12:30.186 --> 12:31.693
You're jo-- You're joking?

12:31.796 --> 12:33.241
No. Oh, uh...

12:33.273 --> 12:35.208
Right here. On your--

12:35.400 --> 12:37.102
Yeah, you just have a little.
Right there.

12:37.983 --> 12:38.999
You got it.

12:40.199 --> 12:41.594
See, that's kinda
what I'm talking about.

12:41.900 --> 12:44.507
(GASPS)

12:44.776 --> 12:47.812
Yeah. I just don't think
you got it.

12:48.907 --> 12:50.125
To be blunt.

12:52.611 --> 12:54.892
What I will say, though,
you coming in here?

12:55.801 --> 12:57.236
I wouldn't have expected that
out of you.

12:57.261 --> 12:58.287
That took some balls.

12:58.630 --> 12:59.749
Oh, yeah.

13:02.401 --> 13:03.661
You know, I got an idea.

13:05.277 --> 13:06.811
Yeah, I tell you
what I'm gonna do.

13:07.687 --> 13:11.234
You know we have the Bangkok
merger coming up, right?

13:12.351 --> 13:13.427
Yes.

13:14.112 --> 13:15.146
Right, so...

13:15.981 --> 13:17.228
I want you on that plane.

13:18.184 --> 13:20.618
We still got outstanding issues
with Appendix-D.

13:20.894 --> 13:23.907
You take a crack at that,
solve it. Prove me wrong.

13:26.005 --> 13:27.090
That sounds fair to me.

13:27.914 --> 13:28.916
- You'll--
- Great.

13:29.575 --> 13:30.736
I'm glad we had this talk.

13:34.613 --> 13:35.629
Boom.

13:36.695 --> 13:38.040
Oh, hello.

13:38.190 --> 13:39.866
- ZURI: Hello.
- BRADLEY: Hey, sexy. Wow.

13:39.891 --> 13:41.759
Am I disturbing anything?

13:41.784 --> 13:43.798
No, no, no, we're just
wrapping it up. Hi, baby.

13:43.823 --> 13:45.311
- My God, this dress.
- Thank you.

13:45.336 --> 13:46.391
- Mmm.
- (KISSES)

13:46.904 --> 13:49.440
Uh, Linda,
this is my fiancée, Zuri.

13:49.515 --> 13:50.716
Lovely to meet you.

13:53.518 --> 13:54.782
Happy fiancée.

13:55.314 --> 13:57.794
Uh, yeah. I am. Thank you?

13:58.600 --> 14:00.491
Linda's one of
our best and brightest.

14:00.631 --> 14:01.749
Thanks for stopping in.

14:01.860 --> 14:03.085
- Nice to meet you.
- Yeah, sure.

14:03.110 --> 14:05.146
Oh, Linda, before you go.
Uh...

14:05.517 --> 14:08.693
Forgot to mention. I've received
a few complaints about you.

14:09.908 --> 14:11.432
- Complaints?
- Yes.

14:11.457 --> 14:14.224
Noxious odors,
I think was the term.

14:14.249 --> 14:17.385
Uh... Tuna fish? Does that
ring a bell? At the desk.

14:18.190 --> 14:21.378
Company policy. Just...
Lunch, it's for the break room.

14:22.100 --> 14:24.102
It's a workplace.
People are trying to focus.

14:24.242 --> 14:25.477
The odors,
they can be...

14:25.598 --> 14:26.833
- a distraction.
- Mm-hmm.

14:28.220 --> 14:29.222
You understand?

14:30.375 --> 14:31.415
Understood.

14:35.186 --> 14:37.146
- MAN: That was bad.
- WOMAN: Right?

14:37.513 --> 14:41.145
(SNIFFLING)

