(CHUCKLES) There you are.

36:00.591 --> 36:02.685
I got scared for a second
you weren't coming back.

36:03.114 --> 36:05.606
Found tracks.
I think it was a boar.

36:05.903 --> 36:08.106
A boar.
Isn't that like a dangerous pig?

36:08.131 --> 36:09.183
It might save us.

36:09.208 --> 36:10.576
(SCRAPING)

36:10.601 --> 36:13.874
Could be a couple more days
before a boat comes.

36:13.899 --> 36:14.907
What is that?
What are you doing?

36:14.932 --> 36:16.407
Might have to last even a week.

36:17.295 --> 36:18.907
We need more sustaining food.

36:19.310 --> 36:20.611
Are you gonna hunt a boar?

36:22.086 --> 36:23.800
Linda from Accounting?

36:25.410 --> 36:28.707
- Strategy and Planning actually.
- Whatever.

36:28.986 --> 36:32.396
But, wait,
shouldn't you know that?

36:33.611 --> 36:38.936
After you looked through so much
of my "very impressive work"?

36:40.390 --> 36:41.429
Was that it?

36:41.572 --> 36:44.883
Before passing me over
for my promotion.

36:44.975 --> 36:47.544
Yeah. Listen,
gotta make the tough call

36:48.093 --> 36:49.719
sometimes, being the boss man.

36:50.013 --> 36:51.714
- You can understand.
- Save it.

36:56.160 --> 36:57.961
(DISTANT ANIMAL CALLS)

37:06.297 --> 37:09.043
(CREATURE SQUEALING)

37:12.310 --> 37:15.089
- (CRACKS)
- (CREATURE SQUEALS)

37:18.875 --> 37:19.983
(GASPS)

37:30.783 --> 37:33.227
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

37:43.607 --> 37:45.207
Where'd you go, piggy?

37:54.391 --> 37:57.794
- Oh.
- (RUSTLING)

37:58.182 --> 37:59.811
(GASPING)

38:03.026 --> 38:05.403
(WHISPERS) Okay. Okay.

38:05.909 --> 38:07.682
(PANTING)

38:08.973 --> 38:10.395
- (DEEP GRUNT)
- (GASPS)

38:12.088 --> 38:14.991
- (GASPS)
- (BOTH SQUEAL)

38:16.721 --> 38:18.817
(SHRIEKING)

38:25.929 --> 38:28.881
(ROARING, GRUNTING)

38:28.906 --> 38:34.525
(SNIFFING)

38:36.580 --> 38:39.035
(SLURPING)

38:39.904 --> 38:42.552
(SHOUTS)

38:42.987 --> 38:45.256
(WAILS)

38:45.448 --> 38:46.476
(GASPS)

38:49.533 --> 38:52.529
- (GRUNTS, GASPS)
- (SCREECHES)

38:52.554 --> 38:55.426
(SCREAMS)

38:55.451 --> 38:58.035
(ROARS)

39:00.057 --> 39:01.971
(PANTS, GRUNTS)

39:02.705 --> 39:06.705
(PANTING, GRUNTING
LAUGHING)

39:06.911 --> 39:09.273
- (BOAR SQUEALING)
- (SCREAMS)

39:09.847 --> 39:13.314
- No! (SCREAMING)
- (GROWLING)

39:13.339 --> 39:17.802
- (SCREAMING)
- (ROARING, GRUNTING)

39:19.356 --> 39:24.198
- (SCREAMING)
- (SQUEALING)

39:26.978 --> 39:29.347
(SCREAMS)

39:29.794 --> 39:31.227
(ROARS)

39:31.275 --> 39:33.082
(GASPING)

39:36.974 --> 39:39.200
(GASPING)

39:39.383 --> 39:42.604
(PANTING)

39:43.281 --> 39:44.415
You ever hunt?

39:45.103 --> 39:48.531
(PANTING)

39:49.200 --> 39:50.434
(WHISPERS) I think I like it.

39:51.875 --> 39:55.182
(PANTING)

39:56.500 --> 39:58.236
- BRADLEY: Mmm.
- LINDA: Mmm.

39:58.922 --> 40:01.825
(BOTH MOANING)

40:02.913 --> 40:05.510
That is the greatest meat
I have ever tasted.

40:05.889 --> 40:08.805
- It's incredible.
- Mmm. (LAUGHS)

40:10.787 --> 40:11.830
(LAUGHS)

40:13.324 --> 40:14.628
(CACKLES)

40:15.593 --> 40:17.161
- What?
- (LAUGHS)

40:18.448 --> 40:19.916
I was just thinking...

40:22.180 --> 40:24.782
While you were sitting here
like a bump on a log...

40:24.915 --> 40:25.935
Mmm?

40:26.604 --> 40:28.841
...little old me was
bringing home the bacon.

40:32.477 --> 40:34.422
- (SARCASTIC CHUCKLE)
- (LAUGHS)

40:37.994 --> 40:41.344
(LAUGHING)

40:41.369 --> 40:43.530
(LAUGHING)

40:44.421 --> 40:45.522
You did.

40:47.305 --> 40:50.741
You-- You literally brought
it home. The bacon.

40:50.766 --> 40:54.742
(CACKLES, SNORTS)

40:54.798 --> 40:59.036
You just snorted. (LAUGHS)

40:59.061 --> 41:00.521
Who's the bacon now?

41:08.171 --> 41:11.174
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

41:27.191 --> 41:30.094
Oh! (LAUGHS, CHEERS)

41:52.702 --> 41:54.027
(CHUCKLES)

42:03.490 --> 42:05.283
(GIGGLES)

42:10.988 --> 42:13.045
(SIGHING)

42:20.390 --> 42:23.515
(INHALES DRAMATICALLY)

42:31.809 --> 42:35.946
(RUMBLING)

42:37.328 --> 42:41.932
- (SHRIEKS)
- (RUMBLING)

42:41.957 --> 42:43.002
Hel--

42:47.310 --> 42:50.177
(SIGHS)

42:52.015 --> 42:53.049
Not yet.

42:58.609 --> 42:59.710
(SIGHS)

43:04.307 --> 43:05.342
Howdy.

43:06.010 --> 43:07.043
Oh, howdy.

43:07.391 --> 43:08.723
What'd I miss out here?

43:08.805 --> 43:10.127
Not a whole lot.

43:11.895 --> 43:14.364
- Where have you been?
- Exploring.

43:14.698 --> 43:16.800
- Found a new water source.
- Great.

43:17.180 --> 43:19.515
Oh, got an iced frappe there?

43:20.864 --> 43:23.400
So much cleaner. So delicious.
Give it a try.

43:24.808 --> 43:26.601
Love the backpack.
You make that today?

43:26.626 --> 43:28.107
Yeah! What do you think?

43:28.498 --> 43:30.091
- Isn't that cute?
- Mmm.

43:31.128 --> 43:32.240
It's super cute.

43:35.112 --> 43:36.747
Okay, what's the matter?

43:37.001 --> 43:38.343
What do you think is the matter?

43:39.996 --> 43:43.035
We've been here,
what, two weeks now?

43:43.820 --> 43:45.122
How have they not found us yet?

43:45.396 --> 43:46.764
I don't know.

43:47.817 --> 43:50.610
I mean, I'm sure it'll be soon.

43:52.103 --> 43:54.907
Anyway, you know what
the most important thing is

43:55.012 --> 43:56.297
for human survival?

43:56.599 --> 43:58.334
The number one thing.

43:59.977 --> 44:01.110
Positive attitude.

44:01.135 --> 44:02.637
Oh, are you fucking kidding me?

44:03.112 --> 44:04.797
We have to act, all right?

44:05.082 --> 44:06.815
I'm serious.
I'm sick of this shit.

44:07.117 --> 44:08.707
We have to do something, okay?

44:08.732 --> 44:10.711
We should build a raft
or something.

44:10.807 --> 44:12.202
- A what?
- Yeah.

44:12.227 --> 44:13.592
I saw a 60 Minutes once

44:13.829 --> 44:15.352
of this guy,
he survived a shipwreck.

44:15.377 --> 44:16.499
He said he did three things.

44:16.524 --> 44:19.508
He saved food and water,
and he got found, okay?

44:19.904 --> 44:22.307
We have to go to where
the boats are, okay?

44:22.338 --> 44:25.208
We gotta-- We gotta find
shipping lanes. Get seen.

44:25.702 --> 44:26.736
Build a raft.

44:26.824 --> 44:28.342
I don't think
that's a good idea.

44:29.079 --> 44:30.665
A raft would be...

44:31.388 --> 44:35.008
I mean, I guess that's
an option, but as a last resort.

44:36.193 --> 44:37.235
No.

44:37.701 --> 44:39.387
We gotta keep doing
what we're doing.

44:40.671 --> 44:41.693
Stay the course.

44:43.074 --> 44:46.778
And anyway, honestly,
is it that bad?

44:47.480 --> 44:50.728
We have food, water, company.

44:51.701 --> 44:52.758
Linda, no disrespect,

44:52.783 --> 44:55.615
but this is the last place
on Earth that I'd want to be.

45:00.183 --> 45:01.251
Ouch.

45:02.673 --> 45:04.241
Haven't I taken
good care of you?

45:04.266 --> 45:05.619
Have you taken good care of me?

45:06.223 --> 45:07.548
Have you seen my face?

45:08.478 --> 45:10.514
Do you think my skin
is going to recover from this?

45:11.007 --> 45:14.257
- Huh?
- Look at you! You're thriving.

45:14.898 --> 45:16.933
(LAUGHS)

45:16.958 --> 45:19.277
This has turned into your life.
Yeah.

45:19.843 --> 45:21.311
What? What are you doing?

45:21.819 --> 45:22.678
I'm getting out of here.

45:22.703 --> 45:24.476
You can't put that kind
of weight on that, yet.

45:24.501 --> 45:26.782
You don't tell me what to do!
How about that?

45:26.807 --> 45:29.172
(GRUNTING)

45:29.206 --> 45:32.218
You know what?
You think you're so smart.

45:33.216 --> 45:34.622
Well, guess who
you're talking to?

45:35.691 --> 45:37.821
CEO of
a NextGen 500 company, baby.

45:38.182 --> 45:40.240
- That's right.
- (LAUGHS)

45:40.577 --> 45:42.691
A company your father built.

45:42.973 --> 45:44.448
God rest his soul.

45:45.389 --> 45:47.605
- (BOTH CHUCKLE)
- Oh, wow.

45:48.369 --> 45:49.929
Oh, wow, you know what?

45:50.001 --> 45:51.802
- You're so done.
- Huh?

45:51.841 --> 45:53.410
Yeah, you're so fired.

45:53.435 --> 45:54.703
Oh, am I?

45:54.728 --> 45:57.437
- Yeah.
- Oh, no. (GIGGLES)

45:58.701 --> 46:01.104
- Where are you going?
- Wherever the fuck I wanna go.

46:01.371 --> 46:03.076
- Making my own camp.
- Oh.

46:03.101 --> 46:04.102
It's not so hard.

46:04.221 --> 46:06.937
Just need some leaves
and some fucking sticks.

46:07.518 --> 46:08.728
I've seen you do it enough.

46:09.593 --> 46:12.243
Well, I wish you luck.

46:12.402 --> 46:14.709
And I'll tell you where
to send my last check.

46:15.699 --> 46:17.513
Second coconut tree on the left.

46:19.015 --> 46:20.067
That's a good rock.

46:22.472 --> 46:23.506
Good tree.

46:24.407 --> 46:25.508
Good foundation.

46:28.297 --> 46:29.693
This will be my home.

46:45.996 --> 46:47.148
Now we're cookin'.

47:25.001 --> 47:26.075
Ha!

47:28.799 --> 47:30.901
(HUMMING)

47:32.676 --> 47:35.412
- (BUGS BUZZING)
- (GRUNTING, PANTING)

47:35.437 --> 47:39.419
Oh, mmm. Mmm.

47:46.169 --> 47:48.112
(GRUNTS)

47:50.680 --> 47:51.804
(LAUGHS)

48:02.586 --> 48:04.765
(PANTING, GRUNTING)

48:13.497 --> 48:15.803
(HUMMING)

48:16.019 --> 48:17.053
Morning!

48:17.513 --> 48:19.066
(CHUCKLES SARCASTICALLY)
Hi.

48:23.086 --> 48:24.154
"Hepl"?

48:30.687 --> 48:31.739
(GROANS)

48:32.489 --> 48:33.525
(SIGHS)

48:37.795 --> 48:40.094
(GASPS)

48:41.598 --> 48:44.200
(GRUNTS)

48:51.595 --> 48:53.995
(PANTING)

48:54.324 --> 48:57.227
- (DELIRIOUS CHUCKLING)
- (CRUNCHES)

48:57.321 --> 48:59.256
Mmm. Mmm.

49:04.194 --> 49:06.513
(WHEEZING, CACKLING)

49:09.085 --> 49:11.156
(GAGGING)

49:11.181 --> 49:12.689
(COUGHING)

49:13.890 --> 49:17.748
(RETCHING, SCREAMING)

49:18.168 --> 49:19.700
(SPITS)

49:20.323 --> 49:21.755
(GROANS)

49:22.286 --> 49:23.954
(WHEEZES, SPITS)

49:24.587 --> 49:27.824
(EXHALING)

49:30.393 --> 49:32.417
(PANTING)

49:32.902 --> 49:34.096
You're beat.

49:39.388 --> 49:41.329
(HUMMING)

49:44.601 --> 49:46.877
(GASPING)
Hello.

49:49.005 --> 49:50.014
BRADLEY: Hello.

49:50.273 --> 49:51.277
Knock, knock.

49:52.028 --> 49:53.059
Hey.

49:53.663 --> 49:54.664
Linda?

49:55.198 --> 49:56.303
- LINDA: Mmm.
- Is that you?

49:56.593 --> 49:59.051
I think we met at
the Christmas party last year.

50:00.397 --> 50:02.834
Oh. Yes. I remember you.

50:02.859 --> 50:04.207
- Yes. Thought that was you.
- Mr. Preston?

50:04.232 --> 50:05.573
Yeah. That's right. How are you?

50:05.598 --> 50:06.799
- I'm great.
- (CHUCKLES)

50:06.824 --> 50:08.626
Oh, you have
a... something in your...

50:08.651 --> 50:10.234
Mmm.

50:10.594 --> 50:11.681
Oh, dear.

50:11.802 --> 50:14.382
(EXOSKELETON CRUNCHING)

50:14.407 --> 50:15.682
- Yeah.
- (SPITS)

50:16.486 --> 50:18.722
Wow. Check out the spread, huh?

50:18.989 --> 50:21.551
You know, I've paid
small fortunes for sushi

50:21.576 --> 50:22.777
that doesn't look that good.

50:23.193 --> 50:24.877
- Oh.
- Yeah.

50:24.902 --> 50:26.074
How much would you pay now?

50:26.099 --> 50:27.978
Oh. I'd kill for
what's on that plate.

50:28.009 --> 50:29.031
Mmm.

50:29.056 --> 50:30.558
But then what would you do
tomorrow?

50:30.895 --> 50:31.986
(LAUGHS)

50:32.382 --> 50:33.417
- Oops.
- Got me there.

50:33.442 --> 50:34.594
(LINDA CHUCKLES)

50:35.973 --> 50:37.475
- Mmm.
- Where did you get the knife?

50:37.526 --> 50:38.599
Oh!

50:39.175 --> 50:40.879
- I found it.
- (CHUCKLES)

50:41.098 --> 50:44.243
It is amazing the things
that just wash up on shore.

50:45.515 --> 50:46.728
Been a real lifesaver.

50:49.084 --> 50:50.152
So...

50:51.114 --> 50:53.616
What brings you
to my office today?

50:55.365 --> 50:56.699
I want to apologize.

50:57.694 --> 50:58.985
- What?
- Just for, uh...

50:59.395 --> 51:00.525
...the way that I acted.

51:01.004 --> 51:02.906
Here? Or when
we were back at your office?

51:02.931 --> 51:03.966
Both.

51:04.501 --> 51:06.345
I wanna take it all back.
Everything I said.

51:06.997 --> 51:08.131
So, I'm not fired?

51:08.156 --> 51:10.392
An asset like you?
Are you kidding me? (CHUCKLES)

51:11.254 --> 51:13.023
The company would be
in shambles without you.

51:13.541 --> 51:15.476
- Look at this place.
- Well, that is a relief.

51:15.786 --> 51:17.120
- Gotta say.
- Yeah. I'm glad.

51:18.088 --> 51:19.101
This looks amazing.

51:19.126 --> 51:21.514
You... look great.

51:21.539 --> 51:23.098
If you don't mind me saying.
Uh...

51:23.123 --> 51:24.178
I don't.

51:24.661 --> 51:27.034
Not even the same person who
walked into my office that day.

51:28.184 --> 51:31.577
So, would you say
you underestimated me?

51:31.602 --> 51:32.636
Yeah.

51:33.197 --> 51:35.733
I would say
I gravely underestimated you.

51:35.758 --> 51:36.924
That's exactly right.

51:37.281 --> 51:38.422
I was wrong.

51:39.202 --> 51:42.380
And I really, really
want to come back to camp.

51:42.405 --> 51:43.454
Hmm.

51:43.593 --> 51:46.006
And learn from you,
if you would have me, of course.

51:47.304 --> 51:49.822
(PANTING)

51:49.847 --> 51:53.113
(GULPING, EXHALES)

51:53.669 --> 51:57.245
Really? Well, I think
we could discuss that.

51:57.867 --> 51:59.435
- Okay.
- Would you like to sit down?

51:59.460 --> 52:01.283
- I would love to.
- Before you fall down.

52:01.308 --> 52:04.287
(CHUCKLES, GRUNTS)

52:05.621 --> 52:07.766
- I was just thinking, you know...
- Mm-hmm?

52:08.978 --> 52:12.054
I want to help.
As much as I can, I mean.

52:12.396 --> 52:14.531
I learned the hard way. You
make all this look really easy.

52:14.556 --> 52:16.644
But, I think
that's the best bet.

52:16.669 --> 52:17.677
Working as a team.

52:18.408 --> 52:20.878
You know?
That's a smart, smart play.

52:20.903 --> 52:21.945
That is smart.

52:21.976 --> 52:23.044
- Yes.
- Yes.

52:23.313 --> 52:26.299
Definitely smart on your part.
(CLEARS THROAT)

52:26.330 --> 52:28.666
"Linda." (WHEEZING LAUGH)

52:31.315 --> 52:32.349
So, what do you think?

52:32.595 --> 52:33.629
About what?

52:34.004 --> 52:35.720
Could you overlook
some of my character flaws?

52:35.745 --> 52:37.013
Of which there are many.

52:37.038 --> 52:39.097
(LAUGHS) And...

52:41.210 --> 52:43.212
...maybe I can join you
for lunch.

52:44.787 --> 52:47.226
Mmm. I don't know.

52:47.810 --> 52:48.930
Can I trust ya?

52:50.987 --> 52:53.480
- You can. (GROANING)
- (SLURPING)

52:56.719 --> 52:57.764
(GROANS)

52:58.015 --> 52:59.323
There was a little more on that.

53:01.584 --> 53:02.785
Linda, please.

53:03.100 --> 53:04.736
(WHISPERING) Please. Please.

53:06.194 --> 53:08.526
I'm sorry. (SIGHS)

53:10.607 --> 53:11.638
So, is that it?

53:13.748 --> 53:15.188
- Was that it?
- Is that your pitch?

53:18.602 --> 53:20.622
What do you want from me? Huh?

53:21.798 --> 53:22.911
Well, that depends.

53:24.887 --> 53:28.855
How above and beyond
are you willing to go for me?

53:34.924 --> 53:35.943
Hmm.

53:53.809 --> 53:56.531
Oh, I'm kidding, I'm kidding.
Just keep your shirt on.

53:56.873 --> 53:58.838
I would never do that.

54:01.097 --> 54:02.332
I'm not like you.

54:06.176 --> 54:07.793
(SIGHS) Enough.

54:09.091 --> 54:10.626
- Eat.
- (EXHALES)

54:11.775 --> 54:13.477
- (CACKLES)
- Enjoy.

54:13.502 --> 54:15.204
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you.

54:15.245 --> 54:17.047
- Here's some sauce.
- Thank you. Thank you.

54:17.072 --> 54:18.730
And I will get you
some more water.

54:18.755 --> 54:20.124
Thank you. (MOANS)

54:20.149 --> 54:22.504
- Mr. Bossypants.
- (MOANING) Oh, my God.

54:23.173 --> 54:26.554
What is that? (MOANS)

54:26.897 --> 54:28.607
Mmm.

54:30.893 --> 54:33.678
Mmm.

54:33.703 --> 54:34.718
Fuck.

54:35.799 --> 54:37.242
Ooh, mama.

54:43.479 --> 54:44.530
BRADLEY: (GRUNTING)

54:45.007 --> 54:47.139
Ah, what do you say
we take a walk?

54:48.595 --> 54:50.093
- Sure.
- Your leg's getting so much better.

54:50.118 --> 54:51.419
We should keep rehabbing it.

54:51.484 --> 54:52.539
Where are we going?

54:53.167 --> 54:54.196
Surprise.

54:56.485 --> 54:57.922
- You okay?
- Yeah.

54:57.947 --> 55:00.429
(BOTH PANTING)

55:18.814 --> 55:20.315
Okay, this spot's tough.

55:23.079 --> 55:24.736
This is the tricky bit.

55:27.891 --> 55:29.139
BRADLEY: (CLEARS THROAT)

55:30.098 --> 55:31.519
- You got it?
- (GRUNTING)

55:35.042 --> 55:36.641
- You got it.
- (GRUNTS)

55:36.666 --> 55:38.630
(BRIGHTLY) There we go.

55:39.382 --> 55:41.811
- Yeah.
- (CHUCKLES) Fun, right?

55:42.484 --> 55:43.731
- (CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)
- (CHUCKLES)

55:43.756 --> 55:44.790
Sure.

55:48.225 --> 55:50.382
(WIND WHISTLING)

55:55.090 --> 55:56.307
Nothing for days.

55:57.968 --> 55:59.039
(SIGHS)

55:59.396 --> 56:00.933
That's us down there.

56:02.271 --> 56:03.365
This way.

56:06.823 --> 56:08.825
(BIRDS SQUAWKING)

56:11.213 --> 56:12.669
Little foraging tip.

56:14.223 --> 56:16.985
So, you never want to
eat a berry

56:18.087 --> 56:19.923
that's yellow, green, or white.

56:20.109 --> 56:22.538
But if you really wanna know
if it's poisonous or not...

56:29.799 --> 56:32.603
If there's a reaction,
like that?

56:32.682 --> 56:35.098
Yeah, yeah. Don't spread it
on your morning scone, got it.

56:35.918 --> 56:37.515
(CHUCKLES) Funny.

56:37.894 --> 56:39.735
All right, now down there,

56:40.203 --> 56:42.265
you see that rock
that kinda looks like an X?

56:42.290 --> 56:43.331
Yeah.

56:43.573 --> 56:45.091
So, that part of the island,

56:45.282 --> 56:48.197
it's all thorn bushes
and poison vines.

56:48.778 --> 56:49.943
Three steps into that,

56:49.968 --> 56:52.593
and you'll be scratching
your skin off for a week, so...

56:53.769 --> 56:55.337
you don't want to
go that way, ever.

56:56.645 --> 56:57.704
Okay.

56:57.729 --> 56:58.730
Okay.

56:59.341 --> 57:00.567
All right. We should head back.

57:00.592 --> 57:01.601
Yeah.

57:02.806 --> 57:03.923
LINDA: Limpy McGee.

57:06.215 --> 57:08.663
(WIND HOWLING)

57:08.688 --> 57:11.536
I might give, uh, my leg
a breather for a minute.

57:13.008 --> 57:14.100
- BRADLEY: (SIGHS)
- Yep.

57:15.116 --> 57:16.192
Take your time.

57:18.367 --> 57:19.835
Big trek down-- (SCREAMS)

57:19.860 --> 57:20.928
Oh, shit!

57:20.953 --> 57:24.572
- (SHOUTING)
- (SCREAMING)

57:24.603 --> 57:26.705
Oh, shit! Shit, here!

57:26.730 --> 57:29.342
- (SCREAMING)
- Here. Grab on.

57:29.879 --> 57:30.914
Grab my hand.

57:30.960 --> 57:32.817
- (SHRIEKING)
- Over here, grab on.

57:32.849 --> 57:34.689
(GROANING)

57:34.714 --> 57:35.727
(GROANS)

57:39.376 --> 57:42.771
- (STRAINING)
- LINDA: (SHOUTING)

57:42.802 --> 57:46.006
(BOTH GRUNTING, PANTING)

57:47.095 --> 57:48.118
BRADLEY: Are you okay?

57:48.891 --> 57:49.893
Thank you.

57:50.794 --> 57:51.795
I owed you one.

57:52.462 --> 57:55.332
(CHUCKLING)

57:58.808 --> 58:00.143
LINDA: Look what I found.

58:00.490 --> 58:01.646
BRADLEY: Green bananas?

58:02.004 --> 58:03.253
Not for long.

58:06.403 --> 58:08.872
Gonna give Mother Nature
a little kick start.

58:12.415 --> 58:14.828
The heat turns the starch
to sugar.

58:16.426 --> 58:17.961
Try one now.

58:26.488 --> 58:27.623
Oh, my God.

58:27.648 --> 58:29.617
- Yeah?
- Oh, it's incredible.

58:29.679 --> 58:32.150
- Mmm.
- It's unbelievable. It's like...

58:32.795 --> 58:34.558
It's crispy, it's creamy.

58:34.583 --> 58:36.300
But, this is nothing.

58:37.586 --> 58:38.754
You ever heard of pruno?

58:39.208 --> 58:40.542
Pruno? What's that?

58:40.583 --> 58:43.151
It's what people in prison
drink to get intoxicated.

58:43.176 --> 58:44.191
Mmm.

58:44.581 --> 58:45.882
Mostly fermented fruit.

58:46.789 --> 58:48.372
It's otherwise known
as "toilet wine."

58:48.397 --> 58:49.431
Toilet wine.

58:50.380 --> 58:51.863
So, what?
You want to make toilet wine?

58:52.882 --> 58:54.010
Already did.

58:55.090 --> 58:56.744
Been working on it
for a few days.

58:57.807 --> 58:58.842
Wanna get drunk?

58:59.395 --> 59:00.430
Fuck yeah.

59:00.776 --> 59:01.835
All right.

59:02.392 --> 59:04.695
BRADLEY: (GARGLING)

59:04.720 --> 59:06.873
LINDA: (LAUGHING)

59:07.003 --> 59:09.013
BRADLEY: (CHORTLES)

59:09.071 --> 59:10.379
It's so good.

59:10.404 --> 59:11.732
Thank you, Sweetie.

59:12.113 --> 59:13.188
Just call me sweetie?

59:14.183 --> 59:15.184
I...

59:15.679 --> 59:18.300
Yes, but...
Sorry, Sweetie's my bird.

59:18.688 --> 59:20.080
Oh, you have a bird.

59:20.610 --> 59:22.484
- Yeah, I miss her.
- Yeah, I bet.

59:22.799 --> 59:24.241
Great little bird.

59:24.467 --> 59:26.634
So, you live alone with a bird?
(LAUGHS)

59:26.738 --> 59:27.873
Sorry. (CHUCKLES)

59:28.296 --> 59:29.341
Sorry.

59:31.975 --> 59:33.004
I was married.

59:33.998 --> 59:35.205
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

59:35.230 --> 59:36.243
Wow.

59:37.887 --> 59:38.746
- Yes.
- Not like that.

59:38.771 --> 59:39.950
I just meant, didn't know.

59:39.975 --> 59:40.983
(SCOFFS) Thanks.

59:41.277 --> 59:42.721
Yeah, ten years.

59:44.987 --> 59:46.599
- Yeah.
- So divorced or...?

59:47.015 --> 59:48.051
No, he died.

59:49.591 --> 59:50.726
Oh, I'm sorry.

59:50.751 --> 59:53.235
No, no. Don't be.
He was not very nice.

59:54.531 --> 59:55.428
Yeah. I just...

59:55.453 --> 59:57.796
I don't think
he knew how to love.

59:58.221 --> 59:59.255
Yeah.

01:00:00.002 --> 01:00:02.171
Yeah, I know how that feels.
(CLEARS THROAT)

01:00:02.371 --> 01:00:03.420
Oh, yeah?

01:00:03.985 --> 01:00:05.005
Yeah.

01:00:06.082 --> 01:00:07.583
Yeah, my parents, uh...

01:00:08.203 --> 01:00:09.238
...were the same.

01:00:09.712 --> 01:00:11.150
Both with each other and me.

01:00:11.960 --> 01:00:13.383
Dad was a total stranger.

01:00:14.624 --> 01:00:16.726
I didn't know him. Couldn't
tell you one thing about him.

01:00:18.327 --> 01:00:19.728
Was raised by my mom.

01:00:20.989 --> 01:00:22.291
Very mean person.

01:00:23.792 --> 01:00:25.627
Uh, like, abusive.

01:00:26.181 --> 01:00:28.016
Emotionally, physically.

01:00:30.820 --> 01:00:32.789
Yeah. Her father was
a piece of shit though,

01:00:32.814 --> 01:00:35.083
so, I try not to blame her, but,

01:00:35.404 --> 01:00:38.760
it's hard to not resent her,
you know?

01:00:44.914 --> 01:00:46.731
You ever hear that saying, uh,

01:00:47.003 --> 01:00:49.283
"monsters aren't born,
they're created"?

01:00:51.214 --> 01:00:52.296
(CHUCKLES)

01:00:52.615 --> 01:00:54.722
Yeah. What?
Are you calling me a monster?

01:00:55.965 --> 01:00:57.500
Oh, yeah.
You're a monster, all right.

01:00:57.880 --> 01:01:00.971
(CHUCKLES)
Yeah. Yeah, I am.

01:01:01.416 --> 01:01:02.583
I am.

01:01:03.298 --> 01:01:04.923
At least now we know...

01:01:06.189 --> 01:01:09.125
...it's not your fault.
(CHUCKLES)

01:01:15.023 --> 01:01:17.230
Did you ever think about
leaving him? Your husband?

01:01:19.934 --> 01:01:20.960
BRADLEY: Yeah.

01:01:22.237 --> 01:01:23.371
Every night.

01:01:24.980 --> 01:01:26.079
For years.

01:01:29.419 --> 01:01:32.810
I just kept hoping
he'd change, and...

01:01:33.614 --> 01:01:36.985
...just go back to how it was
in the beginning. (SCOFFS)

01:01:38.186 --> 01:01:40.217
You know, you just,
you lie to yourself,

01:01:40.242 --> 01:01:43.141
because you don't
want to be alone.

01:01:48.858 --> 01:01:49.962
How'd he die?

01:01:53.243 --> 01:01:54.464
Car accident.

01:01:58.307 --> 01:01:59.596
He was a drinker.

01:02:02.208 --> 01:02:03.506
And, uh...

01:02:05.081 --> 01:02:07.684
...I'd always hide his keys when
he got really, really drunk.

01:02:09.965 --> 01:02:12.667
And one night...
well, that night...

01:02:13.810 --> 01:02:15.124
we had a big fight.

01:02:17.306 --> 01:02:19.545
And he did some things
he shouldn't have.

01:02:22.165 --> 01:02:23.366
Awful things.

01:02:26.195 --> 01:02:27.230
Even for him.

01:02:30.480 --> 01:02:33.399
And he had
this full head of steam.

01:02:34.297 --> 01:02:36.343
He was looking for those keys.

01:02:40.081 --> 01:02:41.661
So, I took them out of my purse.

01:02:44.073 --> 01:02:45.247
Put them on the table.

01:02:47.863 --> 01:02:48.927
Let him go.

01:02:51.393 --> 01:02:52.900
Poured him his last drink.

01:03:02.791 --> 01:03:03.963
Can't believe I told you that.

01:03:03.988 --> 01:03:05.610
- (CHUCKLES)
- It's okay.

01:03:08.084 --> 01:03:09.418
I've never told anyone that.

01:03:19.296 --> 01:03:20.297
You know what?

01:03:21.203 --> 01:03:22.909
I don't think
we should ever leave here.

01:03:25.614 --> 01:03:26.732
You know what I mean?

01:03:45.581 --> 01:03:48.016
(GASPS, GROANS)

01:03:48.806 --> 01:03:51.842
(GROANING)

01:03:58.894 --> 01:04:01.540
Oh, God. (GROANS)

01:04:03.213 --> 01:04:04.353
(STRAINED GROAN)

01:04:12.595 --> 01:04:13.653
(GROANS)

01:04:22.011 --> 01:04:23.112
(SIGHS)

01:04:47.499 --> 01:04:50.721
(DISTANT RUMBLING)

01:04:50.746 --> 01:04:53.000
(WIND ROARING)

01:04:58.621 --> 01:05:01.194
(SHOUTS) Here, cover the fire!

01:05:03.519 --> 01:05:06.301
- (WIND ROARING)
- (THUNDER CRASHING)

01:05:06.326 --> 01:05:09.385
Uh, we gotta get off this beach!

01:05:09.410 --> 01:05:11.829
(CRACKING)

01:05:12.474 --> 01:05:14.013
- (GRUNTING)
- LINDA: (SHOUTS)

01:05:15.638 --> 01:05:16.872
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

01:05:17.066 --> 01:05:18.162
We gotta go!

01:05:18.187 --> 01:05:20.011
(WIND ROARING)

01:05:20.036 --> 01:05:22.348
- Come on!
- (BOTH GRUNTING)

01:05:23.053 --> 01:05:25.229
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:05:25.875 --> 01:05:26.969
LINDA: Oh.

01:05:28.591 --> 01:05:29.712
In here!

01:05:30.426 --> 01:05:33.087
Ready? Okay. Watch your step.

01:05:33.589 --> 01:05:35.758
It gets real low here
so, careful.

01:05:36.029 --> 01:05:37.422
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:05:38.707 --> 01:05:41.544
- LINDA: (GROANS)
- BRADLEY: (PANTING)

01:05:42.706 --> 01:05:44.807
Okay.
This'll be good till it passes.

01:05:47.009 --> 01:05:48.475
It's fucking freezing.

01:05:48.500 --> 01:05:50.012
Take that off. Take it off.

01:05:50.993 --> 01:05:52.050
It'll help.

01:05:52.567 --> 01:05:54.645
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:05:54.957 --> 01:05:57.066
- Okay. Okay. Okay.
- BRADLEY: (SHIVERING)

01:06:00.336 --> 01:06:02.572
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:06:03.086 --> 01:06:05.648
(GASPING)

01:06:08.271 --> 01:06:10.325
Here. Come here.

01:06:11.206 --> 01:06:12.755
Body heat, right?

01:06:13.182 --> 01:06:15.172
Yeah, that's smart. Okay.

01:06:19.001 --> 01:06:21.286
- Okay.
- Yeah, that's better.

01:06:24.399 --> 01:06:27.910
(BOTH PANTING)

01:06:31.206 --> 01:06:35.291
(SIGHS) Okay. (PANTING)

01:06:39.708 --> 01:06:40.776
(GRUNTS)

01:06:42.730 --> 01:06:43.816
Bradley?

01:06:49.853 --> 01:06:51.087
Bradley!

01:06:54.035 --> 01:06:55.219
Bradley?

01:06:57.466 --> 01:06:58.508
Yeah.

01:07:03.605 --> 01:07:04.706
You got up early.

01:07:06.109 --> 01:07:07.341
Yeah, uh...

01:07:08.002 --> 01:07:09.104
Couldn't sleep.

01:07:10.112 --> 01:07:12.948
I went to camp,
and, uh, it's all gone.

01:07:12.973 --> 01:07:14.619
All washed away.

01:07:14.696 --> 01:07:17.436
Probably pretty stupid of me
to build so close to shore.

01:07:17.599 --> 01:07:18.642
No, it's okay.

01:07:18.907 --> 01:07:19.935
Build a new one.

01:07:21.743 --> 01:07:22.762
Yeah.

01:07:22.787 --> 01:07:24.355
Do it on higher ground
this time, right?

01:07:24.799 --> 01:07:25.876
Yeah.

01:07:25.999 --> 01:07:27.082
And I can help.

01:07:27.383 --> 01:07:29.946
I mean, getting stronger.

01:07:31.273 --> 01:07:32.325
Could do it together.

01:07:35.216 --> 01:07:36.351
I'd like that.

01:08:10.592 --> 01:08:11.693
You know, this would be
a lot easier

01:08:11.718 --> 01:08:12.779
if I could use that knife.

01:08:14.896 --> 01:08:15.900
Yeah.

01:08:16.384 --> 01:08:18.615
But you should really
learn to do it without.

01:08:19.982 --> 01:08:22.155
Take a crack at it, solve it.

01:08:22.180 --> 01:08:23.248
Prove me wrong.

01:08:23.418 --> 01:08:24.854
Didn't you say that to me once?

01:08:25.354 --> 01:08:27.657
Ah. Very good.

01:08:30.112 --> 01:08:31.154
(SIGHS)

01:08:31.826 --> 01:08:32.877
All right.

01:08:34.196 --> 01:08:36.732
Leg's getting a little stiff.
I'm gonna take it for a walk.

01:08:37.380 --> 01:08:38.890
I think I'm gonna try to
get to the high ridge today.

01:08:40.296 --> 01:08:42.431
- That's pretty far.
- (SIGHS)

01:08:42.604 --> 01:08:44.987
Watch out for those poison vines
on the south side, remember?

01:08:45.012 --> 01:08:46.014
Yup.

01:08:46.327 --> 01:08:47.327
You know what?

01:08:47.663 --> 01:08:48.712
I'll join you.

01:08:50.298 --> 01:08:51.328
BRADLEY: Sure.

01:08:51.713 --> 01:08:53.477
Need some exercise myself.

01:08:54.603 --> 01:08:56.560
BRADLEY: Hey, I wanted
to thank you, by the way.

01:08:56.586 --> 01:08:57.653
LINDA: For?

01:08:58.081 --> 01:09:00.181
BRADLEY: Just all the things
you've taught me out here.

01:09:00.795 --> 01:09:01.958
Just in case, you know,

01:09:02.271 --> 01:09:05.137
they find us soon,
or this comes to an end.

01:09:05.901 --> 01:09:08.896
Wanted you to know
the time here, for me,

01:09:09.151 --> 01:09:10.219
it wasn't wasted.

01:09:12.314 --> 01:09:14.084
Yeah. I feel the same way.

01:09:18.160 --> 01:09:19.186
(CHUCKLES)

01:09:21.609 --> 01:09:22.610
Can I make you dinner?

01:09:23.825 --> 01:09:24.829
Tomorrow night?

01:09:26.095 --> 01:09:27.496
Get you outta the kitchen
for a change?

01:09:27.521 --> 01:09:28.464
- (CHUCKLES)
- What do you think?

01:09:28.603 --> 01:09:30.639
Well, that would be nice.

01:09:42.191 --> 01:09:44.921
Good evening, madam. Thank you
for dining with us tonight.

01:09:45.114 --> 01:09:47.134
LINDA:
Oh, my goodness. Look at that!

01:09:47.165 --> 01:09:49.127
For starters,
we have a mango salsa,

01:09:49.164 --> 01:09:51.834
accompanied by Marian plums,
freshly picked.

01:09:52.281 --> 01:09:53.881
And for the main course,
we have a beautiful white fish.

01:09:53.906 --> 01:09:57.371
A smoked barramundi
with a wild lemon grass garnish.

01:09:57.446 --> 01:09:58.551
(CHUCKLES)

01:10:00.289 --> 01:10:02.224
W-Wonderful.

01:10:02.517 --> 01:10:03.565
Bon appétit.

01:10:04.219 --> 01:10:07.046
Uh, do you,
do you cook much at home or...?

01:10:07.071 --> 01:10:08.883
No. No. Never.

01:10:08.991 --> 01:10:13.155
We either order out
or go to dinner.

01:10:13.180 --> 01:10:15.750
Occasionally, we'll have
like a chef come and cook for us

01:10:15.775 --> 01:10:17.441
- if we wanna get fancy.
- Wow. Mmm.

01:10:17.901 --> 01:10:21.393
That's you and your fiancée,
Zuri?

01:10:22.925 --> 01:10:23.977
Zuri, yeah.

01:10:25.600 --> 01:10:26.840
You must miss her, huh?

01:10:28.290 --> 01:10:29.311
Yeah.

01:10:39.435 --> 01:10:40.449
You okay?

01:10:42.792 --> 01:10:44.727
(GROANS) Feeling a little, uh...

01:10:47.682 --> 01:10:49.427
(ECHOING) ...dizzy, actually.

01:10:50.485 --> 01:10:52.535
(ECHOING)
Maybe you should lay down.

01:10:52.881 --> 01:10:54.818
(ECHOING) Yeah.

01:10:56.464 --> 01:11:01.354
(GROANS)

01:11:01.794 --> 01:11:03.147
(COUGHING)

01:11:04.513 --> 01:11:06.557
(INTENSE GROANING)

01:11:11.693 --> 01:11:14.228
(GASPING) What?

01:11:14.483 --> 01:11:16.047
(GROANING)

01:11:22.210 --> 01:11:23.761
LINDA: (GROANING)

01:11:24.120 --> 01:11:25.641
(LAUGHS)

01:11:26.763 --> 01:11:31.627
(GROANS) No!

01:11:33.111 --> 01:11:35.075
(PANTING)

01:11:46.582 --> 01:11:48.547
(GRUNTS)

01:11:53.695 --> 01:11:58.172
(SHOUTS, CACKLES)

01:11:58.526 --> 01:11:59.894
Yes!

01:12:00.170 --> 01:12:01.505
Fuck you, Linda!

01:12:01.530 --> 01:12:02.780
(COUGHING)

01:12:05.334 --> 01:12:08.562
(GRUNTING)

01:12:08.712 --> 01:12:10.700
(GRUNTS)

01:12:11.474 --> 01:12:12.606
No, no, no, no!

01:12:13.595 --> 01:12:15.223
Fuck! (GRUNTS)

01:12:16.618 --> 01:12:17.486
(GASPS)

01:12:19.260 --> 01:12:20.267
(SCREAMS)

01:12:21.977 --> 01:12:23.712
(GROANING)

01:12:34.570 --> 01:12:36.617
(GROANS)

01:12:54.496 --> 01:12:55.864
Aw...

01:12:56.017 --> 01:12:57.552
baby.

01:12:59.766 --> 01:13:01.253
(RETCHES)

01:13:06.295 --> 01:13:07.318
(GROANS)

01:13:11.793 --> 01:13:13.360
(GRUNTING)

01:13:13.501 --> 01:13:15.007
LINDA: (GRUNTING)

01:13:17.693 --> 01:13:18.710
BRADLEY: (MUMBLES)

01:13:19.694 --> 01:13:21.563
(RETCHES)

01:13:23.451 --> 01:13:24.434
(GRUNTS)

01:13:24.459 --> 01:13:25.994
(PANTING)

01:13:32.915 --> 01:13:33.975
(GRUNTING)

01:13:38.394 --> 01:13:41.053
I really was just trying
to knock you out. I wasn't...

01:13:41.883 --> 01:13:43.585
I swear to God, you know...

01:13:44.692 --> 01:13:45.985
I wasn't trying to...

01:13:46.010 --> 01:13:47.800
- LINDA: Just stop.
- It was just...

01:13:47.825 --> 01:13:50.732
You don't have to keep
saying that. I-I believe you.

01:13:50.757 --> 01:13:51.772
Mmm.

01:13:53.094 --> 01:13:54.138
LINDA: (EXHALES)

01:13:55.323 --> 01:13:56.367
(SOBS)

01:13:59.100 --> 01:14:01.725
LINDA: I tasted something
bitter, but I just... (SCOFFS)

01:14:02.978 --> 01:14:04.322
I really didn't want to think

01:14:04.347 --> 01:14:05.942
you could
do something like that.

01:14:06.755 --> 01:14:07.850
But...

01:14:09.304 --> 01:14:10.340
Anyway, you know what,

01:14:10.365 --> 01:14:12.380
it would take a hell of a lot
more berries than that to...

01:14:12.794 --> 01:14:13.895
kill a human being.

01:14:14.282 --> 01:14:15.323
Yeah.

01:14:15.704 --> 01:14:16.739
LINDA: For next time.

01:14:16.764 --> 01:14:19.500
I even screwed that up.
(CHUCKLES)

01:14:19.800 --> 01:14:20.901
Such an idiot.

01:14:21.096 --> 01:14:24.189
- BRADLEY: (CRYING)
- (SHUSHING)

01:14:26.515 --> 01:14:27.549
It's okay.

01:14:27.997 --> 01:14:29.341
- I get it.
- (SOBS)

01:14:29.505 --> 01:14:31.005
Here, here, here.

01:14:31.687 --> 01:14:33.966
Come on, let's get
your strength back, huh?

01:14:34.695 --> 01:14:35.743
Again.

01:14:36.284 --> 01:14:37.370
(WHIMPERING) Okay.

01:14:39.154 --> 01:14:40.555
- There you go.
- Mmm.

01:14:40.889 --> 01:14:41.914
Yeah.

01:14:43.364 --> 01:14:44.370
(SIGHS)

01:14:44.974 --> 01:14:48.444
Now, some things are gonna
have to change with you.

01:14:49.391 --> 01:14:51.501
- And it's not gonna be easy.
- Definitely.

01:14:51.574 --> 01:14:52.595
Yeah.

01:14:53.502 --> 01:14:55.878
(GROANS)
I've really been thinking

01:14:56.592 --> 01:14:58.608
how I can get through to you.

01:14:59.294 --> 01:15:00.694
Do you want some?
You haven't eaten.

01:15:01.416 --> 01:15:02.784
I'm okay, thanks.

01:15:02.809 --> 01:15:04.211
- You sure?
- Yeah.

01:15:04.512 --> 01:15:06.012
Still have a queasy tummy.

01:15:06.900 --> 01:15:07.904
Right.

01:15:09.425 --> 01:15:10.560
- I know how hard...
- So stupid.

01:15:10.585 --> 01:15:12.038
...this all must be for you.

01:15:13.288 --> 01:15:14.923
Not being in control.

01:15:15.597 --> 01:15:16.825
- Ahh.
- You're not used to...

01:15:17.693 --> 01:15:19.846
- (CLICKING TONGUE)
- being in this, shall we say,

01:15:20.875 --> 01:15:23.870
- ...submissive position.
- (CLICKING TONGUE)

01:15:24.687 --> 01:15:27.597
I mean, it's natural for you not
to be able to take orders from me.

01:15:27.628 --> 01:15:30.843
To have to depend on me
for your survival.

01:15:31.119 --> 01:15:32.287
- You know?
- (WHEEZES)

01:15:33.414 --> 01:15:34.488
It's just natural.

01:15:34.936 --> 01:15:36.708
You're a slave to your biology.

01:15:36.898 --> 01:15:38.525
- (GURGLE)
- Oh!

01:15:40.009 --> 01:15:41.844
Feeling kinda funny, huh?

01:15:42.598 --> 01:15:44.421
- Can't move?
- (WHEEZES)

01:15:44.793 --> 01:15:48.387
That's the neurotoxins
from this blue-ringed octopus.

01:15:49.684 --> 01:15:53.147
Blocks the transmission
of nerve impulses.

01:15:54.883 --> 01:15:56.407
Caught it about a week ago.

01:15:57.386 --> 01:16:00.461
Was really hoping I wouldn't
have to use it, but...

01:16:01.183 --> 01:16:02.384
...held on to it.

01:16:03.712 --> 01:16:04.913
Just in case.

01:16:06.888 --> 01:16:08.011
(SIGHS)

01:16:08.731 --> 01:16:11.667
Now, you did a great job
with that raft. I gotta say.

01:16:11.900 --> 01:16:13.342
You really are a quick study.

01:16:14.570 --> 01:16:16.921
But if you really wanted it
to hold...

01:16:17.318 --> 01:16:18.480
(SLURS INDISTINCTLY)

01:16:18.573 --> 01:16:21.737
...you should have used
double floor lashing.

01:16:23.231 --> 01:16:24.812
But, of course,
I never taught you that one.

01:16:25.407 --> 01:16:26.478
Shoot.

01:16:27.689 --> 01:16:28.724
(SIGHS)

01:16:29.224 --> 01:16:32.760
Now, I just want to put
your mind at ease, okay?

01:16:33.708 --> 01:16:36.878
The toxins from the
Hapalochlaena lunulata

01:16:37.492 --> 01:16:38.551
aren't gonna kill you.

01:16:39.815 --> 01:16:41.825
And I promise
they will wear off.

01:16:42.504 --> 01:16:44.619
But right now, you won't be able
to move or feel anything.

01:16:45.600 --> 01:16:47.222
And trust me...
(SIGHS)

01:16:47.616 --> 01:16:49.168
...I think you want it that way.

01:16:49.998 --> 01:16:51.099
Ooh.

01:16:59.854 --> 01:17:00.955
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

01:17:02.216 --> 01:17:03.295
Where was I?

01:17:04.293 --> 01:17:09.047
So, when I was a little girl,
we had this dog.

01:17:09.183 --> 01:17:10.347
BRADLEY: (GRUNTS)

01:17:10.699 --> 01:17:13.835
Very, very naughty dog.
So disobedient.

01:17:13.860 --> 01:17:16.738
- (WHIMPERS)
- Always running away.

01:17:18.707 --> 01:17:19.775
(GRUNTS)

01:17:19.806 --> 01:17:23.405
And my dad said,
"It's not his fault.

01:17:23.430 --> 01:17:26.088
(CHUCKLES)
He just..."

01:17:26.139 --> 01:17:27.340
(GRUNTS)

01:17:28.597 --> 01:17:31.231
(SIGHS)
"...needs to be fixed."

01:17:36.983 --> 01:17:37.992
Now...

01:17:39.595 --> 01:17:42.103
- it's actually quite a simple...
- (METAL SCRAPES)

01:17:43.197 --> 01:17:44.519
...medical procedure.

01:17:44.827 --> 01:17:48.229
They used to do it
all the time to Egyptian slaves.

01:17:48.790 --> 01:17:51.506
Made them more, um, obedient.

01:17:52.419 --> 01:17:53.905
- Compliant.
- (WHIMPERS)

01:17:56.911 --> 01:17:57.917
(WHISPERS) Okay.

01:18:00.595 --> 01:18:01.930
No help is coming.

01:18:03.785 --> 01:18:05.920
This is the way things are now.

01:18:06.208 --> 01:18:08.143
And you need
to just accept that.

01:18:09.904 --> 01:18:11.300
You are stuck.

01:18:12.214 --> 01:18:13.416
No power.

01:18:13.802 --> 01:18:15.825
Low end of the totem pole.

01:18:17.065 --> 01:18:19.000
With some asshole boss.

01:18:19.968 --> 01:18:21.303
Just like I was.

01:18:22.303 --> 01:18:23.707
Although, I'm betting...

01:18:23.992 --> 01:18:27.399
I am a much nicer boss
than you ever would have been.

01:18:29.591 --> 01:18:32.527
(GASPS)
Except for maybe this part.

01:18:35.430 --> 01:18:36.514
Ready?

01:18:38.287 --> 01:18:40.093
(MUFFLED WHINING)

01:18:40.895 --> 01:18:43.264
- (GASPS)
- (SQUELCHING)

01:18:43.618 --> 01:18:45.028
- Okay.
- (MUFFLED YELP)

01:18:45.053 --> 01:18:46.378
Now, now, don't be a baby.

01:18:46.403 --> 01:18:47.829
You're not gonna miss
this stuff.

01:18:49.316 --> 01:18:51.170
- (KNIFE CLINKS)
- (SUSTAINED YELP)

01:18:51.753 --> 01:18:52.890
(YELPS)

01:18:53.737 --> 01:18:56.850
- (KNIFE SLICING)
- (MUFFLED WAILING)

01:18:56.881 --> 01:18:58.348
- (WAILS)
- Ooh!

01:18:58.373 --> 01:19:00.514
(MUFFLED WAILING)

01:19:00.539 --> 01:19:02.467
(CHUCKLES)
We got a bleeder here.

01:19:02.492 --> 01:19:04.737
- (YELPS)
- (BRIGHTLY) A lot of blood.

01:19:04.762 --> 01:19:06.415
- (GROANING)
- (CHUCKLING) Wow.

01:19:06.574 --> 01:19:10.411
(GROANING)

01:19:10.436 --> 01:19:11.504
Oh.

01:19:12.727 --> 01:19:13.794
(SIGHS)

01:19:15.911 --> 01:19:17.446
(MUFFLED CRY)

01:19:18.286 --> 01:19:20.270
- It's okay. It's just a rat.
- (GROANS)

01:19:20.883 --> 01:19:22.224
- (GROANS)
- (RAT SPLATTERS)

01:19:25.700 --> 01:19:27.586
Next time it won't be a rat.

01:19:29.991 --> 01:19:33.624
So, don't ever mistake
my kindness for weakness.

01:19:35.092 --> 01:19:40.207
(GRUNTING)

01:19:48.470 --> 01:19:49.571
Hey, there!

01:19:50.965 --> 01:19:52.008
How goes it?

01:19:55.796 --> 01:19:57.898
Barely talked in two days,
you Gloomy Gus.

01:20:02.303 --> 01:20:04.118
Would it kill you
to give me a little smile?

01:20:12.600 --> 01:20:14.625
Mmm. There it is.

01:20:16.204 --> 01:20:17.773
Tell you what I'm gonna do
to cheer you up.

01:20:18.739 --> 01:20:20.184
I'm gonna go find...

01:20:21.302 --> 01:20:24.620
the juiciest, most beautiful
fruits on this whole island

01:20:24.645 --> 01:20:25.813
and make you a little treat.

01:20:31.613 --> 01:20:33.424
Such a sourpuss.

01:20:33.502 --> 01:20:36.470
Make him a little fire,
and he's gonna come around.

01:20:36.604 --> 01:20:40.411
(ENGINE HUMMING)

01:20:44.599 --> 01:20:45.651
(GASPS)

01:20:49.803 --> 01:20:52.034
ZURI: Hello? Hello?

01:20:52.059 --> 01:20:53.081
Shit.

01:20:55.617 --> 01:20:58.020
Linda! It's me.

01:20:58.045 --> 01:21:00.893
(RAPIDLY) Shit, shit,
shit, shit, shit, shit...

01:21:00.918 --> 01:21:04.722
Oh, my God! We found her!
I did it. I can't believe it.

01:21:04.893 --> 01:21:05.919
Hey.

01:21:07.389 --> 01:21:08.724
- Hey.
- No, no, no.

01:21:08.750 --> 01:21:09.966
(EXAGGERATED GIGGLE)

01:21:09.991 --> 01:21:11.684
- Come here!
- (GIGGLE CONTINUES)

01:21:11.709 --> 01:21:12.750
ZURI: Oh, my God.

01:21:12.880 --> 01:21:14.849
Hi. Hello.

01:21:16.411 --> 01:21:18.446
Is he alive? Is he here?

01:21:18.471 --> 01:21:19.442
How on earth?

01:21:19.467 --> 01:21:21.623
Bradley, is he-- is he here?

01:21:21.648 --> 01:21:22.879
- Yes.
- He is?

01:21:22.904 --> 01:21:24.287
- Yes, he's here.
- Oh, my God.

01:21:24.312 --> 01:21:26.506
- He is here.
- He's alive!

01:21:27.201 --> 01:21:29.105
Even when they called off
the search in this area,

01:21:29.137 --> 01:21:30.312
I never gave up.

01:21:30.337 --> 01:21:32.884
- I couldn't give up.
- That's amazing.

01:21:32.909 --> 01:21:35.221
I hired my own boat,
I did my own search.

01:21:35.488 --> 01:21:37.448
Is he okay? Is he hurt? Is he...

01:21:37.473 --> 01:21:38.875
He's fine.

01:21:39.487 --> 01:21:42.285
- He's so good. He's great.
- Great.

01:21:42.310 --> 01:21:44.252
I can't believe
this is happening.

01:21:44.277 --> 01:21:46.191
- I know.
- (CACKLES)

01:21:46.216 --> 01:21:48.118
Please, can you take me to him?
Right now?

01:21:48.143 --> 01:21:50.112
- I need to see him. Please.
- He's, um...

01:21:50.185 --> 01:21:51.219
Is he just down here?

01:21:51.244 --> 01:21:52.524
- Yes, he's out here.
- Yeah? He is?

01:21:52.549 --> 01:21:53.476
No, no, no.

01:21:53.501 --> 01:21:54.736
- He's not over there.
- Bradley, I'm here!

01:21:54.761 --> 01:21:56.795
- Um--
- Bradley, where are you?

01:21:56.898 --> 01:21:58.099
MAN: Should we follow you?

01:21:59.220 --> 01:22:00.230
This way?

01:22:02.183 --> 01:22:03.247
(SIGHS)

01:22:03.272 --> 01:22:04.413
Should we follow you?

01:22:04.438 --> 01:22:05.513
Uh...

01:22:06.514 --> 01:22:09.510
- I just need to get my stuff.
- You're not gonna need this.

01:22:09.535 --> 01:22:10.563
- (SMACKS)
- Ow.

01:22:10.588 --> 01:22:13.309
- Sorry. Sorry, I just...
- You like mango, right?

01:22:13.881 --> 01:22:15.035
Yeah, I worked really hard.

01:22:15.060 --> 01:22:16.540
We got lots of food on the boat.

01:22:18.879 --> 01:22:19.907
Oh, yum.

01:22:20.801 --> 01:22:21.907
Yum, yum, yum.

01:22:22.410 --> 01:22:23.507
Lead the way.

01:22:24.325 --> 01:22:27.252
So, is it just the two of you?

01:22:28.095 --> 01:22:30.522
Or is there a whole search party
waiting for us?

01:22:30.557 --> 01:22:31.581
MAN: Just us.

01:22:32.513 --> 01:22:35.896
But there will be many people
happy to hear you two are alive.

01:22:36.017 --> 01:22:37.089
Once I radio back.

01:22:37.121 --> 01:22:39.002
You'll be back in your own bed
in no time.

01:22:40.021 --> 01:22:41.908
There's a shortcut
just ahead here.

01:22:52.286 --> 01:22:54.977
ZURI: I bet you can't wait
to return to your life.

01:22:55.081 --> 01:22:58.472
Your job, your family,
your friends.

01:22:58.579 --> 01:23:00.114
(MAN SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

01:23:23.085 --> 01:23:25.270
Uh, shoelace.

01:23:26.280 --> 01:23:27.323
Okay.

01:23:27.911 --> 01:23:30.331
- Just follow the trail.
- ZURI: Yeah.

01:23:30.551 --> 01:23:31.919
I'm right behind you.

01:23:42.890 --> 01:23:45.107
(SLOWED BREATHING)

01:23:51.626 --> 01:23:53.207
(SCREAMS)

01:23:53.707 --> 01:23:55.853
Zuri! Zuri! Zuri! Come on!

01:23:55.878 --> 01:23:58.097
- ZURI: (GRUNTING)
- Grab my hand. Hey. Come on!

01:23:58.587 --> 01:24:01.098
I got you. I got you.
You can do it. You can do it.

01:24:01.123 --> 01:24:02.835
Help me! Help me!

01:24:02.860 --> 01:24:04.863
- ZURI: (GROANS)
- Come on. Come on.

01:24:04.888 --> 01:24:05.888
I got you!

01:24:05.981 --> 01:24:07.274
- Zuri! Come on.
- ZURI: Linda, help us!

01:24:07.299 --> 01:24:09.134
I got you. You can do it.
You can do it.

01:24:09.384 --> 01:24:10.985
I got you. You can do it.

01:24:11.010 --> 01:24:12.645
Man: (GROANING)

01:24:12.670 --> 01:24:13.938
Help me!

01:24:13.988 --> 01:24:15.456
- Linda!
- Linda!

01:24:15.679 --> 01:24:17.115
MAN: Help us!

01:24:17.195 --> 01:24:19.955
ZURI: Linda!

01:24:31.092 --> 01:24:32.226
Dinner.

01:24:33.787 --> 01:24:34.945
Yep.

01:24:38.480 --> 01:24:39.549
(SIGHS)

01:25:17.905 --> 01:25:20.674
(RAIN PATTERING)

01:25:26.688 --> 01:25:28.951
Saw some fresh boar tracks
earlier today.

01:25:30.285 --> 01:25:31.966
We haven't had protein
in awhile.

01:25:33.588 --> 01:25:35.439
Maybe when it clears up
we should go hunting.

01:25:39.306 --> 01:25:40.649
I'm taking a sick day.

01:25:44.058 --> 01:25:45.326
Can't do it on my own.

01:26:20.106 --> 01:26:22.413
(SIGHS)

01:26:28.522 --> 01:26:30.209
ZURI: (DISTANTLY) Linda!

01:26:59.420 --> 01:27:02.508
(GROANS)

01:27:05.787 --> 01:27:08.338
(GASPING)

01:27:18.091 --> 01:27:21.858
(STRAINED GROANS)

01:27:23.598 --> 01:27:26.239
(GASPING)

01:27:32.980 --> 01:27:34.399
(GRUNTING FEEBLY)

01:27:36.684 --> 01:27:38.227
(WAILING) Linda.

01:27:39.721 --> 01:27:41.689
Linda!

01:27:43.171 --> 01:27:45.585
You tried to kill me.

01:27:45.726 --> 01:27:47.438
- No.
- Why?

01:27:48.089 --> 01:27:49.330
(CRYING) Why?

01:27:49.964 --> 01:27:51.772
Why'd you do it?

01:27:53.188 --> 01:27:57.104
(GROANS) Why?
(CRYING)

01:27:57.197 --> 01:27:58.997
Why'd you have to come?

01:27:59.219 --> 01:28:00.616
I'm gonna tell Bradley
everything.

01:28:00.641 --> 01:28:01.542
No.

01:28:01.567 --> 01:28:02.793
- You're a murderer.
- No.

01:28:02.818 --> 01:28:03.900
- You are!
- (SCREAMS)

01:28:03.925 --> 01:28:05.970
(GRUNTING)

01:28:08.369 --> 01:28:09.436
(GASPS)

01:28:15.502 --> 01:28:16.963
(ROARS)

01:28:16.988 --> 01:28:18.589
(SCREAMS)

01:28:36.264 --> 01:28:37.274
(LIGHT SNORT)

01:28:39.186 --> 01:28:42.259
(SNORTING)

01:28:50.771 --> 01:28:53.103
- (CRACKS)
- (SQUEALS)

01:28:53.128 --> 01:28:55.807
Fuck! (GASPING)

01:29:08.703 --> 01:29:10.576
(YELPS)

01:29:11.686 --> 01:29:14.388
(SOBS)

01:29:19.994 --> 01:29:24.950
(SOBS)

01:29:26.701 --> 01:29:28.494
(GUTTURAL SHOUT)

01:29:31.493 --> 01:29:32.970
(SCREAMS)

01:29:35.289 --> 01:29:37.824
(SCREAMS)

01:29:39.194 --> 01:29:41.729
(GRUNTING)

01:29:57.792 --> 01:29:58.822
(SIGHS)

01:30:08.608 --> 01:30:09.663
Where you been?

01:30:12.339 --> 01:30:13.407
Nowhere.

01:30:15.696 --> 01:30:17.564
Take another sick day?

01:30:22.576 --> 01:30:23.744
What is it?

01:30:27.201 --> 01:30:28.302
You know what's happening.

01:30:29.642 --> 01:30:31.110
No, I don't actually.

01:30:31.135 --> 01:30:32.136
You don't?

01:30:32.980 --> 01:30:34.903
I don't. I don't actually.

01:30:35.310 --> 01:30:36.477
Did you kill her?

01:30:40.915 --> 01:30:41.985
Who?

01:30:47.095 --> 01:30:49.745
(PANTING)

01:30:51.312 --> 01:30:52.614
She slipped.

01:30:53.794 --> 01:30:56.750
I was trying to bring her to you
and she got ahead--

01:30:56.775 --> 01:30:57.974
Why didn't you tell me?

01:30:57.999 --> 01:30:59.100
Because I knew
how it would look...

01:30:59.125 --> 01:31:00.513
Why wouldn't you tell me
she came here?

01:31:00.538 --> 01:31:01.519
...and I knew you wouldn't
believe me!

01:31:02.075 --> 01:31:03.477
You wouldn't believe me!

01:31:03.724 --> 01:31:06.112
You're right, I don't.

01:31:06.701 --> 01:31:07.768
I don't believe you.

01:31:09.296 --> 01:31:10.296
(SIGHS)

01:31:11.979 --> 01:31:13.803
It was an accident.

01:31:14.295 --> 01:31:16.497
(GASPS) I swear to you.

01:31:17.404 --> 01:31:19.510
Just like your husband's
death was an accident?

01:31:27.007 --> 01:31:28.019
(EXHALES)

01:31:32.880 --> 01:31:34.025
(NERVOUS CHUCKLE)

01:31:37.291 --> 01:31:38.326
(CHUCKLE)

01:31:42.289 --> 01:31:45.337
(SCREAMING)

01:31:46.506 --> 01:31:47.521
(GROWLS)

01:31:57.271 --> 01:31:58.917
- (PANTING)
- (BIRD SQUAWKS)

01:32:01.982 --> 01:32:05.451
(PANTING)

01:32:20.093 --> 01:32:21.133
(BLADE CLINKS)

01:32:26.620 --> 01:32:29.142
- (SHOUTS)
- (SHOUTS)

01:32:31.199 --> 01:32:33.768
(BOTH GROANING)

01:32:33.793 --> 01:32:37.196
(LOW GROANING)

01:32:39.620 --> 01:32:41.355
(GRUNTS)

01:32:41.469 --> 01:32:43.964
(GAGGING)

01:32:43.989 --> 01:32:45.351
(SHOUTING)

01:32:45.793 --> 01:32:46.944
(GASPS)

01:32:52.319 --> 01:32:54.910
(GRUNTS)

01:32:54.935 --> 01:32:58.470
You motherfucker!
(SHOUTS)

01:32:58.665 --> 01:33:01.430
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:33:02.804 --> 01:33:05.844
- (SCREAMS)
- (YELPS)

01:33:05.869 --> 01:33:08.323
- (BOTH GRUNTING)
- (CRUNCHING)

01:33:08.348 --> 01:33:11.426
(WAILING, SCREAMING)

01:33:11.461 --> 01:33:12.695
Oh, fuck!

01:33:12.819 --> 01:33:13.925
What the fuck?

01:33:13.950 --> 01:33:14.951
(SPLATTERS)

01:33:14.976 --> 01:33:16.844
(BOTH SCREAMING)

01:33:18.545 --> 01:33:20.028
BRADLEY: (GRUNTING)

01:33:20.787 --> 01:33:23.490
(SCREAMS)

01:33:24.425 --> 01:33:25.560
(SCREAMS)

01:33:25.585 --> 01:33:28.554
(WAILING)

01:33:30.584 --> 01:33:31.685
(GRUNTS)

01:33:31.758 --> 01:33:33.952
(BOTH WHEEZING)

01:33:34.092 --> 01:33:36.150
LINDA: (GASPING)

01:33:36.476 --> 01:33:37.945
(GRUNTING)

01:33:39.227 --> 01:33:40.661
(EXHALES ANGRILY)

01:33:41.635 --> 01:33:42.738
(EXHALES)

01:33:43.897 --> 01:33:45.846
(SNICKERS)

01:33:46.519 --> 01:33:47.561
(RING CLICKS)

01:33:50.216 --> 01:33:52.197
(GROWLS)

01:33:58.165 --> 01:34:00.801
(EXHALES)

01:34:01.281 --> 01:34:03.550
Fuck you, Bradley!

01:34:03.575 --> 01:34:04.642
(SHOUTS)

01:34:05.165 --> 01:34:06.466
(SHOUTS)

01:34:08.089 --> 01:34:10.553
(SCREAMS)

01:34:10.585 --> 01:34:12.926
- (SHOUTS)
- (GASPS)

01:34:15.278 --> 01:34:17.438
(GASPING)

01:34:20.587 --> 01:34:22.975
LINDA: (WAILS)

01:34:23.418 --> 01:34:24.683
Oh!

01:34:24.879 --> 01:34:29.037
(SHRIEKING)

01:34:29.436 --> 01:34:30.682
Where'd you go?

01:34:32.399 --> 01:34:33.474
(SIGHS)

01:34:52.519 --> 01:34:54.947
(PANTING)

01:34:57.484 --> 01:35:00.820
BRADLEY: (PANTING)

01:35:06.773 --> 01:35:08.951
(PANTING)

01:35:13.094 --> 01:35:19.278
(PANTING, GRUNTS)

01:35:19.900 --> 01:35:22.976
(GRUNTING) Hey. Hey!

01:35:25.165 --> 01:35:26.166
Hey!

01:35:26.380 --> 01:35:28.505
(GRUNTING)

01:35:28.609 --> 01:35:31.579
Hey! (WHEEZING)

01:35:37.798 --> 01:35:40.743
(GRUNTING)

01:35:40.888 --> 01:35:42.380
- Hey!
- (KNOCKING)

01:35:45.219 --> 01:35:49.565
(GRUNTING)

01:35:51.206 --> 01:35:55.480
(WHEEZING)

01:36:01.168 --> 01:36:03.627
(PANTING, GRUNTS)

01:36:08.988 --> 01:36:12.407
What the fuck? (GASPING)

01:36:13.594 --> 01:36:14.715
(GRUNTS)

01:36:17.491 --> 01:36:19.853
LINDA: Oh, is there anything
more civilized

01:36:19.878 --> 01:36:21.513
than refrigeration?

01:36:22.182 --> 01:36:23.550
(GRUNTING)

01:36:23.575 --> 01:36:25.199
LINDA: There's a frozen
Massaman curry in there

01:36:25.224 --> 01:36:26.330
that's to die for.

01:36:26.355 --> 01:36:27.669
BRADLEY: (GASPING)

01:36:30.278 --> 01:36:31.846
LINDA: You looking for a knife?

01:36:32.585 --> 01:36:35.825
(INHALES) Yeah. I got rid of all
of those.

01:36:36.696 --> 01:36:38.082
(GASPS) Except for one.

01:36:39.893 --> 01:36:41.054
Hey, pal.

01:36:42.396 --> 01:36:44.817
So tell me, Bradley,

01:36:45.092 --> 01:36:48.425
how does a knife
just wash up on shore?

01:36:48.450 --> 01:36:49.467
(CHUCKLES)

01:36:49.796 --> 01:36:51.802
You really crack me up
sometimes.

01:36:51.827 --> 01:36:54.410
- (GRUNTING)
- (SHATTERS)

01:36:55.502 --> 01:36:57.611
Where you going? Where
you going? Where you going?

01:36:58.578 --> 01:36:59.584
Oh, there you are.

01:36:59.653 --> 01:37:00.930
(PANTING)

01:37:00.955 --> 01:37:02.403
LINDA: Nice place, huh?

01:37:03.190 --> 01:37:05.559
Owner is some
Wall Street billionaire.

01:37:06.494 --> 01:37:08.819
First thing I did
was turn off the security.

01:37:09.190 --> 01:37:11.625
Guy didn't even notice.
(CHUCKLES)

01:37:12.706 --> 01:37:15.552
Bradley, I have a confession to
make and I feel sick about it.

01:37:17.184 --> 01:37:18.903
Sorry to tell you this, but...

01:37:19.913 --> 01:37:21.949
we could've been rescued
some time ago.

01:37:24.858 --> 01:37:26.871
But I wasn't
ready to leave yet.

01:37:29.877 --> 01:37:32.012
I just needed
a little more time.

01:37:55.696 --> 01:37:57.497
After the caretakers left...

01:37:58.706 --> 01:38:00.124
I broke in.

01:38:01.475 --> 01:38:03.143
It was easy. (CHUCKLES)

01:38:07.086 --> 01:38:08.955
(WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY)

01:38:12.386 --> 01:38:14.237
(SIGHS)

01:38:24.785 --> 01:38:26.221
(CHUCKLES)

01:38:33.380 --> 01:38:36.835
And then you and me,
we were alone again.

01:38:36.860 --> 01:38:38.568
(PANTING)

01:38:38.651 --> 01:38:41.087
It was... perfect.

01:38:41.901 --> 01:38:43.340
(WHISPERS) What the fuck.

01:38:44.098 --> 01:38:46.603
LINDA:
Just me and my new Sweetie.

01:38:48.489 --> 01:38:51.980
- Well, for a little while.
- (GROANS)

01:38:53.613 --> 01:38:55.416
Things just kept happening.

01:38:57.011 --> 01:38:58.529
It's not like I planned it.

01:39:00.481 --> 01:39:01.748
I swear to you.

01:39:02.909 --> 01:39:04.307
I didn't want any of this.

01:39:04.437 --> 01:39:05.507
ZURI: Linda!

01:39:06.893 --> 01:39:10.290
MAN: Come on, girl!
You can do it, I got you!

01:39:10.570 --> 01:39:13.764
Zuri! Zuri! I got you!
You can do it! You can do it!

01:39:14.815 --> 01:39:16.895
I got you!

01:39:16.920 --> 01:39:21.080
(SCREAMS)
Linda!

01:39:21.105 --> 01:39:23.030
(DEEP INHALE)

01:39:32.620 --> 01:39:33.621
Bradley?

01:39:35.416 --> 01:39:40.410
Don't you wonder why we were
the only ones who made it?

01:39:43.010 --> 01:39:44.935
(RAGGED BREATHING)

01:39:44.960 --> 01:39:48.219
Maybe it was written
in the stars.

01:39:49.984 --> 01:39:51.509
(WHEEZING)

01:39:52.186 --> 01:39:54.368
(PANTING)

01:39:59.006 --> 01:40:03.092
- (SLOW FOOTSTEPS)
- LINDA: (EXHALES)

01:40:08.963 --> 01:40:10.379
(FOOTSTEPS)

01:40:11.209 --> 01:40:12.297
(SHOTGUN COCKS)

01:40:12.322 --> 01:40:13.404
(GRUNTS)

01:40:14.801 --> 01:40:16.906
I'm sorry it had to be this way.

01:40:18.411 --> 01:40:20.247
Because it could've been
so good.

01:40:20.272 --> 01:40:22.600
Wait, wait, please,
please, please. You were right.

01:40:22.677 --> 01:40:24.050
You were right.
You were right, okay?

01:40:24.075 --> 01:40:26.270
I was-- I was a piece of shit.

01:40:26.295 --> 01:40:28.463
- I was a terrible person.
- Uh-huh.

01:40:28.488 --> 01:40:29.923
I was, uh...

01:40:29.948 --> 01:40:33.023
I was a monster.
(WHIMPERING) I was.

01:40:33.887 --> 01:40:38.497
I was a monster! (SOBBING)

01:40:40.580 --> 01:40:44.631
The way I treated everyone.
(SOBS)

01:40:45.886 --> 01:40:48.722
I'm so broken.

01:40:49.662 --> 01:40:51.202
You broke me.

01:40:55.001 --> 01:40:56.369
(WHISPERS) I've changed.

01:40:57.998 --> 01:41:03.801
Really, I have. I can feel it.
(GASPS)

01:41:04.024 --> 01:41:07.394
Because of you. Because I... I--

01:41:08.822 --> 01:41:09.856
Linda...

01:41:12.299 --> 01:41:13.931
I think you're
the most incredible person

01:41:13.956 --> 01:41:14.978
I've ever known.

01:41:17.817 --> 01:41:19.052
You took care of me.

01:41:20.201 --> 01:41:21.312
I tried.

01:41:21.688 --> 01:41:24.346
You did.
And you taught me things.

01:41:26.520 --> 01:41:29.036
No one's ever taken the time
to teach me anything.

01:41:34.186 --> 01:41:35.351
(SIGHS)

01:41:37.490 --> 01:41:38.683
(QUIETLY) You saved me.

01:41:42.903 --> 01:41:46.104
I felt love from you in a way
that I've never...

01:41:46.580 --> 01:41:48.134
felt from anyone.

01:41:49.875 --> 01:41:51.000
(WHIMPERING)

01:41:54.862 --> 01:41:56.616
I think we can make this work.

01:41:58.378 --> 01:42:00.371
- What?
- Here.

01:42:03.503 --> 01:42:04.614
No, you don't.

01:42:05.092 --> 01:42:07.835
Yeah. You were right.
We can stay.

01:42:09.088 --> 01:42:11.312
You proved it yourself
we can survive.

01:42:12.185 --> 01:42:13.705
We have everything we need.

01:42:14.961 --> 01:42:15.994
Yeah.

01:42:17.177 --> 01:42:18.846
That's what I've been saying.

01:42:18.871 --> 01:42:19.872
I know.

01:42:21.094 --> 01:42:23.340
There's nothing for us
back there.

01:42:25.392 --> 01:42:27.427
- I want to be happy.
- (EXHALES)

01:42:27.452 --> 01:42:29.045
With you, here.

01:42:30.490 --> 01:42:32.292
Just us, you and me.

01:42:37.985 --> 01:42:39.100
I see it now.

01:42:39.773 --> 01:42:40.808
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

01:42:43.617 --> 01:42:45.100
(WHISPERS) Actually happy?

01:42:46.105 --> 01:42:47.268
Not some bullshit?

01:42:47.293 --> 01:42:49.032
Not some fucking bullshit.

01:42:50.705 --> 01:42:52.318
You want to go back
to that life?

01:42:52.343 --> 01:42:53.611
No fucking way.

01:42:53.888 --> 01:42:55.808
What would we go back to?

01:42:55.890 --> 01:42:57.514
- Nothing.
- Nothing.

01:42:58.998 --> 01:43:04.219
We stay here, you and me,
forever.

01:43:07.381 --> 01:43:08.582
That sounds...

01:43:10.176 --> 01:43:11.611
...like a fairy tale.

01:43:11.785 --> 01:43:13.793
LINDA: (GIGGLES)

01:43:13.818 --> 01:43:16.219
- (CHUCKLES)
- (GIGGLES)

01:43:18.605 --> 01:43:20.207
I love you so much.

01:43:24.910 --> 01:43:26.592
Why did you make it so hard?

01:43:26.913 --> 01:43:28.060
I'm a fucking idiot.

01:43:28.085 --> 01:43:30.789
(BOTH LAUGH)

01:43:31.484 --> 01:43:33.453
Oh, sorry I gouged your eye out.

01:43:33.478 --> 01:43:35.178
(BOTH LAUGHING)

01:43:35.756 --> 01:43:37.058
Sorry I stabbed you.

01:43:37.110 --> 01:43:40.390
(BOTH LAUGH)

01:43:40.415 --> 01:43:42.616
You did! Oh, you did.

01:43:42.668 --> 01:43:44.271
(CHUCKLES, SNIFFLING)

01:43:44.388 --> 01:43:45.477
God, I love you.

01:43:45.575 --> 01:43:46.951
I love you.

01:43:59.819 --> 01:44:01.619
- BRADLEY: (GRUNTS)
- LINDA: No!

01:44:01.781 --> 01:44:03.741
- (SHOUTS)
- (GRUNTS)

01:44:03.877 --> 01:44:06.180
- (GASPS)
- (GRUNTS)

01:44:06.310 --> 01:44:07.746
(COCKS SHOTGUN)

01:44:07.771 --> 01:44:09.688
Bye, you crazy bitch
from Accounting.

01:44:09.713 --> 01:44:12.522
(WEAKLY) No.
No!

01:44:12.926 --> 01:44:13.928
(CLICKS)

01:44:14.715 --> 01:44:15.775
(RATCHETS)

01:44:16.217 --> 01:44:17.262
(CLICKS)

01:44:18.572 --> 01:44:21.071
Ow! Fuck!

01:44:21.096 --> 01:44:23.943
- (GROANS)
- (SHOUTS)

01:44:27.581 --> 01:44:29.182
Strategy and Planning.

01:44:31.231 --> 01:44:32.332
(GRUNTS)

01:44:33.133 --> 01:44:36.206
(CROWD OOHS)

01:44:36.396 --> 01:44:37.499
Boom.

01:44:41.875 --> 01:44:43.255
This is Polly Perera, here

01:44:43.280 --> 01:44:46.312
at the 19th Annual
Celebrity Golf Invitational.

01:44:46.385 --> 01:44:50.009
And we're here with everyone's
favorite real-life survivor...

01:44:50.096 --> 01:44:51.998
- Linda Liddle.
- (CHUCKLES)

01:44:52.023 --> 01:44:53.324
You're looking
pretty good out here.

01:44:53.349 --> 01:44:56.276
Oh, thanks, Polly.
It's a game I've grown to love.

01:44:56.998 --> 01:44:59.333
Linda, it's been almost a year

01:44:59.358 --> 01:45:01.079
since the world
fell in love with you,

01:45:01.104 --> 01:45:03.687
when you were found
alone at sea on a raft,

01:45:03.712 --> 01:45:07.411
the only survivor of a terrible
plane crash. How did you do it?

01:45:09.135 --> 01:45:11.170
Well, it wasn't easy. (CHUCKLES)

01:45:11.195 --> 01:45:15.299
But the memory
of my lost colleagues is what...

01:45:16.490 --> 01:45:19.239
...drove me forward
and kept me hanging in there.

01:45:20.801 --> 01:45:23.725
Your incredible best-seller
is being turned into a movie.

01:45:23.750 --> 01:45:24.555
(LAUGHS)

01:45:24.580 --> 01:45:26.296
- What's next for you?
- I can't even believe it.

01:45:26.321 --> 01:45:27.914
(LAUGHS)

01:45:27.939 --> 01:45:29.680
So next, uh...

01:45:29.705 --> 01:45:31.797
Well, I'm writing
a self-help book.

01:45:32.786 --> 01:45:34.414
Because I want people to know...

01:45:36.315 --> 01:45:37.689
...no help is coming.

01:45:38.686 --> 01:45:40.608
So you better start
saving yourself.

01:45:43.511 --> 01:45:47.215
("ONE WAY OR ANOTHER"
BY BLONDIE PLAYS)

01:46:02.289 --> 01:46:06.013
♪ One way, or another
I'm gonna find ya ♪

01:46:06.110 --> 01:46:08.235
♪ I'm gonna get ya, get ya,
Get ya, get ya ♪

01:46:08.260 --> 01:46:11.856
♪ One way, or another
I'm gonna win ya ♪

01:46:11.951 --> 01:46:14.082
♪ I'm gonna get ya, get ya
Get ya, get ya ♪

01:46:14.107 --> 01:46:17.799
♪ One way, or another
I'm gonna see ya ♪

01:46:17.824 --> 01:46:20.058
♪ I'm gonna meet ya, meet ya
Meet ya, meet ya ♪

01:46:20.083 --> 01:46:22.219
♪ One day, maybe next week ♪

01:46:22.269 --> 01:46:23.804
♪ I'm gonna meet ya ♪

01:46:23.835 --> 01:46:25.923
♪ I'm gonna meet ya
I'll meet ya ♪

01:46:25.948 --> 01:46:31.979
♪ I will drive
Past your house ♪

01:46:32.113 --> 01:46:37.599
♪ And if the lights
Are all down ♪

01:46:37.624 --> 01:46:43.306
♪ I'll see who's around ♪

01:47:10.083 --> 01:47:14.002
♪ One way, or another
I'm gonna lose ya ♪

01:47:14.027 --> 01:47:15.917
♪ I'm gonna give you the slip ♪

01:47:15.942 --> 01:47:17.350
♪ A slip of the hip ♪

01:47:17.375 --> 01:47:18.514
♪ Or another ♪

01:47:18.539 --> 01:47:19.974
♪ I'm gonna lose ya ♪

01:47:19.999 --> 01:47:22.033
♪ I'm gonna trick ya
I'll trick ya ♪

01:47:22.122 --> 01:47:25.921
♪ One way, or another
I'm gonna lose ya ♪

01:47:25.946 --> 01:47:28.129
♪ I wanna trick ya, trick ya
Trick ya, trick ya ♪

01:47:28.154 --> 01:47:31.757
♪ One way, or another
I'm gonna lose ya ♪

01:47:31.782 --> 01:47:33.890
♪ I'm gonna give you the slip ♪

01:47:39.820 --> 01:47:42.873
♪ I'll walk down the mall
Stand over by the wall ♪

01:47:42.898 --> 01:47:45.801
♪ Where I can see it all
Find out who you call ♪

01:47:45.826 --> 01:47:48.617
♪ Lead you
To the supermarket checkout ♪

01:47:48.642 --> 01:47:51.740
♪ Some specials and rat food
Get lost in the crowd ♪

01:47:51.765 --> 01:47:54.968
♪ One way, or another
I wanna get ya ♪

01:47:54.993 --> 01:47:57.667
♪ Where I can see it all
Find out who you call ♪

01:47:57.692 --> 01:48:00.628
♪ One way, or another
I wanna get ya ♪

01:48:00.659 --> 01:48:03.512
♪ Where I can see it all
Find out who you call ♪

01:48:03.537 --> 01:48:05.789
♪ One way or another ♪

01:48:05.814 --> 01:48:06.920
(MUSIC FADES)
